581 //Autoflow: loadRun_auto
582 void US_ReporterGMP::loadRun_auto ( QMap < QString, QString > & protocol_details )
583 {
584  AProfileGUID = protocol_details[ "aprofileguid" ];
585  ProtocolName_auto = protocol_details[ "protocolName" ];
586  invID = protocol_details[ "invID_passed" ].toInt();
587  runID = protocol_details[ "runID" ];
588  runName = protocol_details[ "experimentName" ];
589  FileName = protocol_details[ "filename" ];
590  intensityID = protocol_details[ "intensityID" ];
591  AutoflowID_auto = protocol_details[ "autoflowID" ];
592  analysisIDs = protocol_details[ "analysisIDs" ];
593  autoflowStatusID = protocol_details[ "statusID" ];
594  optimaName = protocol_details[ "OptimaName" ] ;
595  dataSource = protocol_details[ "dataSource" ] ;
596  expType = protocol_details[ "expType" ] ;
597  simulatedData = false;
598  abde_channList. clear();
599  abde_ranges_percents. clear();
600  abde_rmsd. clear();
601  abde_menisc. clear();
602  abde_plots_filenames. clear();
603  abde_data_per_channel. clear();
604 
605  prot_details_at_report = protocol_details;
606 
607  QString full_runname = protocol_details[ "filename" ];
608  FullRunName_auto = runName + "-run" + runID;
609  if ( full_runname.contains(",") && full_runname.contains("IP") && full_runname.contains("RI") )
610  {
611  QString full_runname_edited = full_runname.split(",")[0];
612  full_runname_edited.chop(3);
613  full_runname = full_runname_edited + " (combined RI+IP) ";
614 
615  FullRunName_auto += " (combined RI+IP) "; //Captures protDev names...
616  }
617 
618  //lb_hdr1 ->setText( QString( tr("Report for run: %1") ).arg(FileName) );
619  lb_hdr1 ->setText( QString( tr("Report for run: %1") ).arg( FullRunName_auto ) );
620  lb_hdr1->setSizePolicy( QSizePolicy::Preferred, QSizePolicy::Fixed );
621 
622  //show progress dialog
623  progress_msg = new QProgressDialog ("Accessing run's protocol...", QString(), 0, 12, this);
624  progress_msg->setWindowFlags(Qt::Tool | Qt::WindowTitleHint | Qt::CustomizeWindowHint);
625  progress_msg->setModal( true );
626  progress_msg->setWindowTitle(tr("Assessing Run's Protocol"));
627  QFont font_d = progress_msg->property("font").value<QFont>();
628  QFontMetrics fm(font_d);
629  int pixelsWide = fm.width( progress_msg->windowTitle() );
630  qDebug() << "Progress_msg: pixelsWide -- " << pixelsWide;
631  progress_msg ->setMinimumWidth( pixelsWide*2 );
632  progress_msg->adjustSize();
633  progress_msg->setAutoClose( false );
634  progress_msg->setValue( 0 );
635  progress_msg->show();
636  qApp->processEvents();
637 
638  progress_msg->setValue( 1 );
639  qApp->processEvents();
640 
641  qDebug() << "1.ExpAborted: " << protocol_details[ "expAborted" ];
642  qDebug() << "1.CorrectRadii: " << protocol_details[ "correctRadii" ];
643 
644  qDebug() << "Exp. Label: " << protocol_details[ "label" ];
645  qDebug() << "GMP Run ? " << protocol_details[ "gmpRun" ];
646 
647  qDebug() << "AnalysisIDs: " << protocol_details[ "analysisIDs" ];
648  qDebug() << "aprofileguid: " << AProfileGUID ;
649 
650 
651  //Now, read protocol's 'reportMask' && reportItems masks && populate trees
652  read_protocol_and_reportMasks( );
653  progress_msg->setValue( 7 );
654  qApp->processEvents();
655 
656  if ( expType == "VELOCITY" )
657  {
658  //check triples for failure
659  check_failed_triples( );
660 
661  //check models existence
662  check_models( AutoflowID_auto.toInt() );
663  progress_msg->setValue( 8 );
664  qApp->processEvents();
665 
666  //identify what's intended to be simulated
667  check_for_missing_models( );
669  }
670 
671  //Check for dropped triples
672  check_for_dropped_triples();
674 
675 
676  //build Trees
677  build_genTree();
678  progress_msg->setValue( 9 );
679  qApp->processEvents();
680 
681  if ( expType == "VELOCITY" )
682  {
683  build_perChanTree();
684  progress_msg->setValue( 10);
685  qApp->processEvents();
686 
687  build_combPlotsTree();
688  progress_msg->setValue( 11 );
689  qApp->processEvents();
690  }
691  else if ( expType == "ABDE" )
692  {
693  build_perChanTree_abde();
694  progress_msg->setValue( 10 );
695  qApp->processEvents();
696  }
697 
698  build_miscTree();
699  progress_msg->setValue( 12 );
700  qApp->processEvents();
701 
702  progress_msg->setValue( progress_msg->maximum() );
703  qApp->processEvents();
704  progress_msg->close();
705 
706  //compose a message on missing models
707  QString msg_missing_models = missing_models_msg();
708 
709  //Inform user that current configuraiton corresponds to GMP report
710  if ( !GMP_report )
711  {
712  QMessageBox::information( this, tr( "Report Profile Uploaded" ),
713  tr( "<font color='red'><b>ATTENTION:</b> There are missing models for certain triples: </font><br><br>"
714  "%1<br><br>"
715  "As a result, a non-GMP report will be generated!")
716  .arg( msg_missing_models) );
717  }
718 
719  //generate report (download models, simulate, create PDFs)
720  generate_report();
721 
722 }

725 //read eSign GMP record for assigned oper(s) && rev(s) && status
726 QMap< QString, QString> US_ReporterGMP::read_autoflowGMPReportEsign_record( US_DB2* db )
727 {
728  QMap< QString, QString> eSign_record;
729 
730  QStringList qry;
731  qry << "get_gmp_review_info_by_autoflowID" << AutoflowID_auto;
732  qDebug() << "read eSing rec, qry -- " << qry;
733 
734  db->query( qry );
735 
736  if ( db->lastErrno() == US_DB2::OK ) // e-Sign record exists
737  {
738  while ( db->next() )
739  {
740  eSign_record[ "ID" ] = db->value( 0 ).toString();
741  eSign_record[ "autoflowID" ] = db->value( 1 ).toString();
742  eSign_record[ "autoflowName" ] = db->value( 2 ).toString();
743  eSign_record[ "operatorListJson" ] = db->value( 3 ).toString();
744  eSign_record[ "reviewersListJson" ] = db->value( 4 ).toString();
745  eSign_record[ "eSignStatusJson" ] = db->value( 5 ).toString();
746  eSign_record[ "eSignStatusAll" ] = db->value( 6 ).toString();
747  eSign_record[ "createUpdateLogJson" ] = db->value( 7 ).toString();
748  eSign_record[ "approversListJson" ] = db->value( 8 ).toString();
749  eSign_record[ "smeListJson" ] = db->value( 9 ).toString();
750 
751  eSign_record[ "isEsignRecord" ] = QString("YES");
752  eSign_record[ "isHistory" ] = QString("NO");
753  }
754  }
755  else
756  {
757  //No record, so no oper/revs assigned!
758  qDebug() << "No e-Sign GMP record exists in main table!!";
759  qDebug() << "Checking History...";
760  qry. clear();
761 
762  qry << "get_gmp_review_info_by_autoflowID_history" << AutoflowID_auto;
763  qDebug() << "read eSing rec HISTORY, qry -- " << qry;
764  db->query( qry );
765 
766  if ( db->lastErrno() == US_DB2::OK ) // e-Sign record exists
767  {
768  while ( db->next() )
769  {
770  eSign_record[ "ID" ] = db->value( 0 ).toString();
771  eSign_record[ "autoflowID" ] = db->value( 1 ).toString();
772  eSign_record[ "autoflowName" ] = db->value( 2 ).toString();
773  eSign_record[ "operatorListJson" ] = db->value( 3 ).toString();
774  eSign_record[ "reviewersListJson" ] = db->value( 4 ).toString();
775  eSign_record[ "eSignStatusJson" ] = db->value( 5 ).toString();
776  eSign_record[ "eSignStatusAll" ] = db->value( 6 ).toString();
777  eSign_record[ "createUpdateLogJson" ] = db->value( 7 ).toString();
778  eSign_record[ "approversListJson" ] = db->value( 8 ).toString();
779  eSign_record[ "smeListJson" ] = db->value( 9 ).toString();
780 
781  eSign_record[ "isEsignRecord" ] = QString("YES");
782  eSign_record[ "isHistory" ] = QString("YES");
783  }
784  }
785  else
786  {
787  eSign_record[ "isEsignRecord" ] = QString("NO");
788  eSign_record. clear();
789  }
790  }
791 
792  return eSign_record;
793 }

796 //form a string of opers/revs out of jsonDoc
797 QString US_ReporterGMP::get_assigned_oper_revs( QJsonDocument jsonDoc )
798 {
799  QString smry;
800  QStringList assigned_list;
801 
802  if ( !jsonDoc. isArray() )
803  {
804  qDebug() << "jsonDoc not a JSON, and/or not an JSON Array!";
805  return smry;
806  }
807 
808  QJsonArray jsonDoc_array = jsonDoc.array();
809  for (int i = 0; i < jsonDoc_array.size(); ++i )
810  assigned_list << jsonDoc_array[i].toString();
811 
812  for ( int ii = 0; ii < assigned_list.count(); ii++ )
813  {
814  smry += assigned_list[ ii ];
815  if ( ii != assigned_list.count() -1 )
816  smry += "; ";
817  }
818 
819  return smry;
820 }

823 //check for dropped triples (at 3. IMPORT)
824 void US_ReporterGMP::check_for_dropped_triples( void )
825 {
826  droppedTriplesList. clear();
827 
828  QStringList dropped_triples_RI, dropped_triples_IP;
829  read_reportLists_from_aprofile( dropped_triples_RI, dropped_triples_IP );
830 
831  for ( int i=0; i<dropped_triples_RI.size(); ++i )
832  droppedTriplesList << dropped_triples_RI[ i ];
833  for ( int i=0; i<dropped_triples_IP.size(); ++i )
834  {
835  QStringList tname = dropped_triples_IP[ i ].split(".");
836  QString tname_mod = tname[0] + "." + "Interference";
837  droppedTriplesList << tname_mod;
838  }
839 
840  qDebug() << "::check_for_dropped_triples(): List of ALL dropped triples : " << droppedTriplesList;
841 
842 }

844 //check for failed triples
845 void US_ReporterGMP::check_failed_triples( void )
846 {
847 
848  US_Passwd pw;
849  US_DB2 db( pw.getPasswd() );
850 
851  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
852  {
853  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
854  tr( "Could not connect to database \n" ) + db.lastError() );
855  return;
856  }
857 
858  QStringList tripleNames;
859 
860  QStringList analysisIDs_list = analysisIDs.split(",");
861  for( int i=0; i < analysisIDs_list.size(); ++i )
862  {
863  QMap <QString, QString> analysis_details;
864  QString requestID = analysisIDs_list[i];
865 
866  qDebug() << "GMP Report: RequestID: " << requestID;
867 
868  analysis_details = read_autoflowAnalysis_record( &db, requestID );
869 
870  if ( !analysis_details.size() )
871  {
872  analysis_details = read_autoflowAnalysisHistory_record( &db, requestID );
873  qDebug() << "GMP Report: analysis_details.size() FROM autoflowAnalysisHistory -- " << analysis_details.size();
874  }
875  else
876  qDebug() << "GMP Report: analysis_details.size() FROM autoflowAnalysis -- " << analysis_details.size();
877 
878  QString triple_name = analysis_details[ "triple_name" ] ;
879  QString cluster = analysis_details[ "cluster" ] ;
880  QString filename = analysis_details[ "filename" ] ;
881  QString curr_gfacID = analysis_details[ "CurrentGfacID" ];
882  QString curr_HPCAnalysisRequestID = analysis_details[ "currentHPCARID"];
883  QString status_json = analysis_details[ "status_json" ] ;
884  QString status = analysis_details[ "status" ] ;
885  QString status_msg = analysis_details[ "status_msg" ] ;
886  QString create_time = analysis_details[ "create_time" ] ;
887  QString update_time = analysis_details[ "update_time" ] ;
888  QString nextWaitStatus = analysis_details[ "nextWaitStatus" ] ;
889  QString nextWaitStatusMsg = analysis_details[ "nextWaitStatusMsg" ] ;
890 
891  qDebug() << "Triple_name, Status -- " << triple_name << status;
892  tripleNames << triple_name;
893 
894  QJsonDocument jsonDoc = QJsonDocument::fromJson( status_json.toUtf8() );
895  if (!jsonDoc.isObject())
896  {
897  qDebug() << "GMP Report: All Doc: NOT a JSON Doc !!";
898 
899  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "JSON Format Problem" ),
900  tr( "JSON message for status of the analysis performed on triple %1 appears to be corrupted. "
901  "This may be an indicaiton of the problem with the analysis run for this triple.\n\n"
902  "This problem will preclude status monitoring for other triples. "
903  "Please check log messages, or contact administrator for help.\n\n"
904  "The program will return to the autoflow runs dialog.").arg( triple_name ) );
905  return;
906  }
907 
908  const QJsonValue &to_process = jsonDoc.object().value("to_process");
909  const QJsonValue &processed = jsonDoc.object().value("processed");
910  const QJsonValue &submitted = jsonDoc.object().value("submitted");
911 
912  QJsonArray to_process_array = to_process.toArray();
913  QJsonArray processed_array = processed.toArray();
914 
915  if ( status == "FAILED" || status == "CANCELED" )
916  {
917  if ( processed.isUndefined())
918  qDebug() << "Nothing has been processed yet !!";
919  else
920  {
921  qDebug() << "analysing last() of processed:" ;
922  //get last() array's element
923  QString stage_failed = processed_array.last().toObject().keys().last();
924 
925  qDebug() << "GMP Report: stage_failed for triple -- " << triple_name << stage_failed;
926 
927  Triple_to_FailedStage[ triple_name ] = stage_failed;
928  }
929  }
930  }
931 
932  //Determine if 'S' data
933  for (int i=0; i< tripleNames.size(); ++i )
934  {
935  if ( tripleNames[i].contains(".S.") )
936  {
937  simulatedData = true;
938  break;
939  }
940  }
941 
942  qDebug() << "[in check_failed().. ] : simulatedData? " << simulatedData;
943 }

1037 //check models existence for a run/protocol loaded
1038 void US_ReporterGMP::check_for_missing_models ( void )
1039 {
1040  bool hasIT = cAP2. job4run; //2dsa-it
1041  bool hasMC = cAP2. job5run; //2dsa-mc
1042  bool hasPCSA = cAPp .job_run; //pcsa
1043 
1044 
1045  QMap < QString, QStringList >::iterator mm;
1046  for ( mm = Triple_to_Models.begin(); mm != Triple_to_Models.end(); ++mm )
1047  {
1048  QStringList missing_models;
1049  qDebug() << "For triple -- " << mm.key() << ", there are models: " << mm.value();
1050 
1051  if ( hasIT && !mm.value().contains( "2DSA-IT" ))
1052  missing_models << "2DSA-IT";
1053  if ( hasMC && !mm.value().contains( "2DSA-MC" ))
1054  missing_models << "2DSA-MC";
1055  if ( hasPCSA && !mm.value().contains( "PCSA" ))
1056  missing_models << "PCSA";
1057 
1058  Triple_to_ModelsMissing[ mm.key() ] = missing_models;
1059  }
1060 
1061  //debug
1062  for ( mm = Triple_to_ModelsMissing.begin(); mm != Triple_to_ModelsMissing.end(); ++mm )
1063  qDebug() << "For triple -- " << mm.key() << ", there are missing models: " << mm.value();
1064 
1065 }
1066 
1067 //Compose a string of missing models
1068 QString US_ReporterGMP::missing_models_msg( void )
1069 {
1070  QString models_str;
1071  int num_dropped_triples = 0;
1072  int num_total_missed_triples = 0;
1073 
1074  QMap < QString, QStringList >::iterator mmm;
1075  for ( mmm = Triple_to_ModelsMissing.begin(); mmm != Triple_to_ModelsMissing.end(); ++mmm )
1076  {
1077  if ( !mmm.value().isEmpty() )
1078  {
1079  ++num_total_missed_triples;
1080  //check if missing models because of triple dropped
1081  bool isDropped = false;
1082  QString c_triple = mmm.key();
1083  c_triple.replace(".","");
1084  for (int i=0; i<droppedTriplesList.size(); ++i)
1085  {
1086  QString d_triple = droppedTriplesList[i];
1087  d_triple.replace(".","");
1088  if ( c_triple == d_triple )
1089  {
1090  ++num_dropped_triples;
1091  isDropped = true;
1092  break;
1093  }
1094  }
1095 
1096  //compose : Do we want to report on dropped triples at all ?
1097  models_str += mmm.key() + ", missing models: " + mmm.value().join(", ");
1098  if( isDropped )
1099  models_str += "<font color='red'> [triple dropped]</font>";
1100 
1101  models_str += "<br>";
1102  }
1103  }
1104 
1105  qDebug() << "Number of total missing triples; Number of dropped triples -- "
1106  << num_total_missed_triples << "; " << num_dropped_triples;
1107 
1108  // Do we want to report on dropped triples at all ?
1109  // Do ONLY dropped triples trigger report to be non-GMP ?
1110  if ( !models_str.isEmpty() & num_total_missed_triples != num_dropped_triples )
1111  GMP_report = false;
1112 
1113  return models_str;
1114 }

1176 //check models existence for a run loaded
1177 void US_ReporterGMP::check_models ( int autoflowID )
1178 {
1179  //build Array of triples
1180  int nchna = currAProf.pchans.count();
1181  for ( int i = 0; i < nchna; i++ )
1182  {
1183  QString channel_desc_alt = chndescs_alt[ i ];
1184  QString channel_desc = chndescs[ i ];
1185 
1186  //check if channel meant to be analyzed/reported
1187  int analysis_to_be_run = analysis_runs[ i ];
1188  int report_to_be_run = report_runs[ i ];
1189 
1190  if ( analysis_to_be_run == 0 || report_to_be_run == 0 )
1191  continue;
1192 
1193  QList < double > chann_wvls = ch_wvls[ channel_desc_alt ];
1194  int chann_wvl_number = chann_wvls.size();
1195 
1196  for ( int jj = 0; jj < chann_wvl_number; ++jj )
1197  {
1198  QString wvl = QString::number( chann_wvls[ jj ] );
1199 
1200  QString tripleName = channel_desc_alt.section( ":", 0, 0 )[0] + "." + channel_desc_alt.section( ":", 0, 0 )[1];
1201 
1202  if ( channel_desc_alt.contains( "Interf" ) )
1203  tripleName += ".Interference";
1204  else
1205  tripleName += "." + wvl;
1206 
1207  //'S' data
1208  if ( dataSource. contains("DiskAUC:Absorbance") && simulatedData )
1209  tripleName = tripleName.replace( ".A.", ".S." );
1210 
1211  qDebug() << "[in check_models()]: TripleName -- " << tripleName;
1212  Array_of_tripleNames.push_back( tripleName );
1213  }
1214  }
1215 
1216  US_Passwd pw;
1217  US_DB2* db = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
1218 
1219  if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
1220  {
1221  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
1222  QMessageBox::information( this,
1223  tr( "DB Connection Problem" ),
1224  tr( "There was an error connecting to the database:\n" )
1225  + db->lastError() );
1226 
1227  return;
1228  }
1229 
1230  //iterate over triples && get eID for each triple's data:
1231  for ( int i=0; i < Array_of_tripleNames.size(); ++ i )
1232  {
1233  QString triple_name_actual = Array_of_tripleNames[ i ];
1234 
1235  if ( triple_name_actual.contains("Interference") )
1236  triple_name_actual.replace( "Interference", "660" );
1237 
1238  //get requestID in autoflowAnalysis based on tripleName & autoflowID
1239  QStringList query;
1240  query << "get_modelAnalysisInfo" << Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] << QString::number( autoflowID );
1241  qDebug() << "check_models qry -- " << query;
1242  db->query( query );
1243 
1244  QString modelDescJson;
1245  while ( db->next() )
1246  {
1247  modelDescJson = db->value( 0 ).toString();
1248  //Triple_to_ModelsDesc[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ] = modelDescJson;
1249 
1250  qDebug() << "Triple, modelDesc -- " << Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] << modelDescJson;
1251  }
1253 
1254  //Now parse modelDecsJson for eID, modelIDs
1255  //Triple_to_ModeslDesc[ "1.A.225" ] [ "2DSA-IT" ] = modelID;
1256  //Triple_to_ModeslDesc[ "1.A.225" ] [ "2DSA-MC" ] = modelID;
1257  //Triple_to_ModeslDesc[ "1.A.225" ] [ "PCSA" ] = modelID;
1258  //Triple_to_ModeslDesc[ "1.A.225" ] [ "eID" ] = eID;
1259  Triple_to_ModelsDesc [ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ] = parse_models_desc_json( modelDescJson, "modelID" );
1260  Triple_to_ModelsDescGuid[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ] = parse_models_desc_json( modelDescJson, "modelGUID" );
1261 
1262 
1263  QString eID = Triple_to_ModelsDesc[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ][ "eID" ];
1264  qDebug() << "In check_models: eID -- " << eID;
1265 
1266  //now check models based on eID:
1267  query.clear();
1268  query << "get_modelDescsIDs" << eID;
1269  db->query( query );
1270 
1271  QStringList model_list;
1272 
1273  while ( db->next() )
1274  {
1275  QString description = db->value( 0 ).toString();
1276  QString modelID = db->value( 1 ).toString();
1277  //QString date = US_Util::toUTCDatetimeText( db->value( 3 ).toDateTime().toString( "yyyy/MM/dd HH:mm" ), true );
1278  QDateTime date = db->value( 2 ).toDateTime();
1279 
1280  QDateTime now = QDateTime::currentDateTime();
1281 
1282  if ( description.contains( "2DSA-IT" ) && modelID == Triple_to_ModelsDesc[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ][ "2DSA-IT" ] )
1283  {
1284  qDebug() << "2DSA-IT Ids: modelID, read from modelLink: " << modelID << Triple_to_ModelsDesc[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ][ "2DSA-IT" ];
1285  model_list << "2DSA-IT";
1286  }
1287 
1288  if ( description.contains( "2DSA-MC" ) && modelID == Triple_to_ModelsDesc[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ][ "2DSA-MC" ] )
1289  {
1290  qDebug() << "2DSA-MC Ids: modelID, read from modelLink: " << modelID << Triple_to_ModelsDesc[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ][ "2DSA-MC" ];
1291  model_list << "2DSA-MC";
1292  }
1293 
1294  if ( description.contains( "PCSA" ) && modelID == Triple_to_ModelsDesc[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ][ "PCSA" ] )
1295  {
1296  qDebug() << "PCSA Ids: modelID, read from modelLink: " << modelID << Triple_to_ModelsDesc[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ][ "PCSA" ];
1297  model_list << "PCSA";
1298  }
1299  }
1300 
1301  //populate QMap connecting triple name to it's existing models
1302  Triple_to_Models[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ] = model_list;
1303  }
1304 
1305  //DEBUG
1306 
1307  //test
1308  delete db;
1309 
1310 }

1312 //Create QMap for shorter desctiption of triple's models (2DSA-IT, ...) to modelIDs, OR to modelGUIDs
1313 QMap< QString, QString > US_ReporterGMP::parse_models_desc_json( QString modelDescJson, QString model_property )
1314 {
1315  QMap <QString, QString> modelDesc_shortened;
1316 
1317  if ( !modelDescJson.isEmpty() )
1318  {
1319  QJsonDocument jsonDoc = QJsonDocument::fromJson( modelDescJson.toUtf8() );
1320  QJsonObject json_obj = jsonDoc.object();
1321 
1322  foreach(const QString& key, json_obj.keys())
1323  {
1324  QJsonValue value = json_obj.value(key);
1325 
1326  qDebug() << "ModelsDesc key, value: " << key << value;
1327 
1328  if ( key == "2DSA_IT" || key == "2DSA_MC" || key == "PCSA" )
1329  {
1330  QString key_mod = key;
1331  key_mod. replace("_","-");
1332 
1333  QJsonArray json_array = value.toArray();
1334  for (int i=0; i < json_array.size(); ++i )
1335  {
1336  foreach(const QString& array_key, json_array[i].toObject().keys())
1337  {
1338  //by modelID
1339  if ( array_key == "modelID" && array_key == model_property )
1340  {
1341  // if ( !modelDesc_shortened.contains( key_mod ) ) //Temporary, for PCSA (2 entries)
1342  // {
1343  modelDesc_shortened[ key_mod ] = json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
1344  qDebug() << "modelDescJson Map: -- model, property, value: "
1345  << key_mod
1346  << array_key
1347  << json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
1348  // }
1349  }
1350 
1351  //by modelGUID
1352  if ( array_key == "modelGUID" && array_key == model_property )
1353  {
1354  if ( !modelDesc_shortened.contains( key_mod ) ) //Temporary, for PCSA (2 entries)
1355  {
1356  modelDesc_shortened[ key_mod ] = json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
1357  qDebug() << "modelDescJson Map: -- model, property, value: "
1358  << key_mod
1359  << array_key
1360  << json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
1361  }
1362  }
1363 
1364  if ( array_key == "editeddataID" )
1365  {
1366  modelDesc_shortened[ "eID" ] = json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
1367  qDebug() << "modelDescJson Map: -- meID, value: "
1368  << array_key
1369  << json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
1370 
1371  }
1372  }
1373  }
1374  }
1375  }
1376  }
1377 
1378  return modelDesc_shortened;
1379 }

1817 int US_ReporterGMP::list_all_autoflow_records( QList< QStringList >& autoflowdata )
1818 {
1819  int nrecs = 0;
1820  autoflowdata.clear();
1821 
1822  QStringList qry;
1823 
1824  US_Passwd pw;
1825  US_DB2* db = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
1826 
1827  if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
1828  {
1829  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "LIMS DB Connection Problem" ),
1830  tr( "Could not connect to database \n" ) + db->lastError() );
1831 
1832  return nrecs;
1833  }
1834 
1835  //Check user level && ID
1836  QStringList defaultDB = US_Settings::defaultDB();
1837  QString user_guid = defaultDB.at( 9 );
1838 
1839  //get personID from personGUID
1840  qry.clear();
1841  qry << QString( "get_personID_from_GUID" ) << user_guid;
1842  db->query( qry );
1843 
1844  int user_id = 0;
1845 
1846  if ( db->next() )
1847  user_id = db->value( 0 ).toInt();
1848 
1849 
1850  //deal with autoflowHistory descriptions
1851  qry. clear();
1852  qry << "get_autoflow_history_desc";
1853  db->query( qry );
1854 
1855  while ( db->next() )
1856  {
1857  QStringList autoflowentry;
1858  QString id = db->value( 0 ).toString();
1859  QString runname = db->value( 5 ).toString();
1860  QString status = db->value( 8 ).toString();
1861  QString optimaname = db->value( 10 ).toString();
1862 
1863  QDateTime time_started = db->value( 11 ).toDateTime().toUTC();
1864  QString invID = db->value( 12 ).toString();
1865 
1866  QDateTime time_created = db->value( 13 ).toDateTime().toUTC();
1867  // QString ptime_created = US_Util::toUTCDatetimeText( time_created
1868  // .toString( Qt::ISODate ), true )
1869  // .section( " ", 0, 0 ).simplified();
1870  QString ptime_created = US_Util::toUTCDatetimeText( time_created
1871  .toString( Qt::ISODate ), true )
1872  .section( ":", 0, 1 ) + " UTC";
1873 
1874 
1875  QString gmpRun = db->value( 14 ).toString();
1876  QString full_runname = db->value( 15 ).toString();
1877 
1878  QString operatorID = db->value( 16 ).toString();
1879  QString devRecord = db->value( 18 ).toString();
1880 
1881  QDateTime local(QDateTime::currentDateTime());
1882 
1883  if ( devRecord == "Processed" )
1884  continue;
1885 
1886  //process runname: if combined, correct for nicer appearance
1887  if ( full_runname.contains(",") && full_runname.contains("IP") && full_runname.contains("RI") )
1888  {
1889  QString full_runname_edited = full_runname.split(",")[0];
1890  full_runname_edited.chop(3);
1891

1893  runname += " (combined RI+IP) ";
1894  }
1895 
1896  autoflowentry << id << runname << optimaname << ptime_created;
1897  //time_created.toString(); // << time_started.toString(); // << local.toString( Qt::ISODate );
1898 
1899  if ( time_started.toString().isEmpty() )
1900  autoflowentry << QString( tr( "NOT STARTED" ) );
1901  else
1902  {
1903  if ( status == "LIVE_UPDATE" )
1904  autoflowentry << QString( tr( "RUNNING" ) );
1905  if ( status == "EDITING" || status == "EDIT_DATA" || status == "ANALYSIS" || status == "REPORT" || status == "E-SIGNATURES" )
1906  autoflowentry << QString( tr( "COMPLETED" ) );
1907  //autoflowentry << time_started.toString();
1908  }
1909 
1910  if ( status == "EDITING" )
1911  status = "LIMS_IMPORT";
1912 
1913  autoflowentry << status << gmpRun;
1914 
1915  //Check user level && GUID; if <3, check if the user is operator || investigator
1916  if ( US_Settings::us_inv_level() < 3 )
1917  {
1918  qDebug() << "User level low: " << US_Settings::us_inv_level();
1919  qDebug() << "user_id, operatorID.toInt(), invID.toInt() -- " << user_id << operatorID.toInt() << invID.toInt();
1920 
1921  //if ( user_id && ( user_id == operatorID.toInt() || user_id == invID.toInt() ) )
1922  if ( user_id && user_id == invID.toInt() )
1923  {//Do we allow operator as defined in autoflow record to also see reports??
1924 
1925  autoflowdata << autoflowentry;
1926  nrecs++;
1927  }
1928  }
1929  else
1930  {
1931  autoflowdata << autoflowentry;
1932  nrecs++;
1933  }
1934 
1935  }
1936 
1937  //test
1938  delete db;
1939 
1940  return nrecs;

2152 //combPlots parms
2153 QMap< QString, QMap< QString, QString > > US_ReporterGMP::parse_comb_plots_json( QString combPlots )
2154 {
2155  QMap< QString, QMap< QString, QString > > iMap;
2156  qDebug() << "combPlots: " << combPlots;
2157  //parse JSON into QMap
2158  if ( !combPlots.isEmpty() )
2159  {
2160  QJsonDocument jsonDoc = QJsonDocument::fromJson( combPlots.toUtf8() );
2161  QJsonObject json_obj = jsonDoc.object();
2162 
2163  foreach(const QString& key, json_obj.keys())
2164  {
2165  QJsonValue value = json_obj.value(key);
2166 
2167  qDebug() << "CombPlots key (type,method), value: " << key << value;
2168 
2169  QJsonArray json_array = value.toArray();
2170  for (int i=0; i < json_array.size(); ++i )
2171  {
2172  foreach(const QString& array_key, json_array[i].toObject().keys())
2173  {
2174  iMap[ key ][ array_key ] = json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
2175 
2176  qDebug() << "ComboPlots Map: -- type_method, parameter, value: "
2177  << key
2178  << array_key
2179  << json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
2180  }
2181  }
2182  }
2183  }
2184 
2185  return iMap;
2186 }

2188 //read Intensity info
2189 QMap< QString, QString > US_ReporterGMP::read_autoflowIntensity( QString ID, US_DB2* db )
2190 {
2191  QString iJson;
2192  QMap< QString, QString > iMap;
2193  QStringList qry;
2194  qry << "read_autoflow_intensity_record" << ID;
2195  db->query( qry );
2196 
2197  qDebug() << "readIntens: qry -- " << qry;
2198 
2199  if ( db->lastErrno() == US_DB2::OK ) // Intensity record exists
2200  {
2201  while ( db->next() )
2202  {
2203  iJson = db->value( 0 ).toString();
2204  }
2205  }
2206 
2207  qDebug() << "iJson: " << iJson;
2208  //parse JSON into QMap
2209  if ( !iJson.isEmpty() )
2210  {
2211  QJsonDocument jsonDoc = QJsonDocument::fromJson( iJson.toUtf8() );
2212  QJsonObject json_obj = jsonDoc.object();
2213 
2214  foreach(const QString& key, json_obj.keys())
2215  {
2216  QJsonValue value = json_obj.value(key);
2217 
2218  if ( value.isString() ) //single-wvl
2219  {
2220  iMap["singlewvl"] = value.toString();
2221  }
2222  else if ( value.isArray() ) //MWL
2223  {
2224  QJsonArray json_array = value.toArray();
2225  for (int i=0; i < json_array.size(); ++i )
2226  {
2227  foreach(const QString& array_key, json_array[i].toObject().keys())
2228  {
2229  iMap[ array_key ] = json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
2230 
2231  qDebug() << "Intensity: MWL -- array_key, val: "
2232  << array_key
2233  << json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
2234  }
2235  }
2236  }
2237  }
2238  }
2239 
2240  return iMap;
2241 }

2243 //parse JSON for general rpeort mask
2244 void US_ReporterGMP::parse_gen_mask_json ( const QString reportMask )
2245 {
2246  QJsonDocument jsonDoc = QJsonDocument::fromJson( reportMask.toUtf8() );
2247  json = jsonDoc.object();
2248 
2249  topLevelItems = json.keys();
2250 
2251  foreach(const QString& key, json.keys())
2252  {
2253  QJsonValue value = json.value(key);

2465

2530 //get Item's children
2531 void US_ReporterGMP::get_item_childs( QList< QTreeWidgetItem* > & children_list, QTreeWidgetItem* item)
2532 {
2533  children_list << item;
2534 
2535  int children = item->childCount();
2536  for ( int i = 0; i < children; ++i )
2537  get_item_childs( children_list, item->child(i) );
2538 }
2539 
2540 //What to check/uncheck upon change in items status
2541 void US_ReporterGMP::changedItem( QTreeWidgetItem* item, int col )
2542 {
2543  //we deal with col 0 only
2544  if ( col != 0 )
2545  return;
2546 
2547  //disconnect
2548  item -> treeWidget() -> disconnect();
2549 
2550  //go over children: recursive search for all children down the tree
2551  int children = item->childCount();
2552  QList< QTreeWidgetItem* > children_list;
2553 
2554  for( int i = 0; i < children; ++i )
2555  get_item_childs( children_list, item->child(i) );
2556 
2557  for ( int i = 0; i < children_list.size(); ++i )
2558  children_list[ i ] -> setCheckState( 0, (Qt::CheckState) item->checkState(0) );
2559 
2560  //Go over parents
2561  QTreeWidgetItem* parent_item = item->parent();
2562  QList< QTreeWidgetItem* > parents_list;
2563  QTreeWidgetItem* current_p_item = new QTreeWidgetItem;
2564 
2565  while ( parent_item )
2566  {
2567  parents_list << parent_item;
2568  current_p_item = parent_item;
2569  parent_item = current_p_item -> parent();
2570  }
2571 
2572  for( int j = 0; j < parents_list.size(); ++j )
2573  {
2574  int checked_children = 0;
2575  int parent_item_children = parents_list[ j ] ->childCount();
2576  for( int jj = 0; jj < parent_item_children; ++jj )
2577  {
2578  if ( int( parents_list[ j ]->child( jj )->checkState(0) ) )
2579  ++checked_children;
2580  }
2581 
2582  if ( checked_children )
2583  parents_list[ j ]->setCheckState( 0, Qt::Checked );
2584  else
2585  parents_list[ j ]->setCheckState( 0, Qt::Unchecked );
2586  }
2587 
2588  //reconnect
2589  connect( item -> treeWidget(), SIGNAL( itemChanged( QTreeWidgetItem*, int ) ),
2590  this, SLOT( changedItem( QTreeWidgetItem*, int ) ) );
2591 }

3926 //read eSign GMP record for assigned oper(s) && rev(s) && status
3927 QMap< QString, QString> US_ReporterGMP::read_autoflowGMPReportEsign_record( QString aID)
3928 {
3929  QMap< QString, QString> eSign_record;
3930 
3931  US_Passwd pw;
3932  US_DB2* db = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
3933 
3934  if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
3935  {
3936  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "LIMS DB Connection Problem" ),
3937  tr( "Could not connect to database \n" ) + db->lastError() );
3938 
3939  return eSign_record;
3940  }
3941 
3942  QStringList qry;
3943  qry << "get_gmp_review_info_by_autoflowID" << aID;
3944  qDebug() << "read eSing rec, qry -- " << qry;
3945 
3946  db->query( qry );
3947 
3948  if ( db->lastErrno() == US_DB2::OK ) // e-Sign record exists
3949  {
3950  while ( db->next() )
3951  {
3952  eSign_record[ "ID" ] = db->value( 0 ).toString();
3953  eSign_record[ "autoflowID" ] = db->value( 1 ).toString();
3954  eSign_record[ "autoflowName" ] = db->value( 2 ).toString();
3955  eSign_record[ "operatorListJson" ] = db->value( 3 ).toString();
3956  eSign_record[ "reviewersListJson" ] = db->value( 4 ).toString();
3957  eSign_record[ "eSignStatusJson" ] = db->value( 5 ).toString();
3958  eSign_record[ "eSignStatusAll" ] = db->value( 6 ).toString();
3959  eSign_record[ "createUpdateLogJson" ] = db->value( 7 ).toString();
3960  eSign_record[ "approversListJson" ] = db->value( 8 ).toString();

4131 DbgLv(1) << "ScMd: m: id,gid,eid,desc" << mmIDs[m] << mmGUIDs[m] << meIDs[m] << mmDescs[m]; }
4132

4134  // cell description by edit ID

4150

4152  { // We have found the data description, so map it
4153  QString ddesc = mxml.mid( kk + 13 );
4154  kk = ddesc.indexOf( "\"" );
4155  ddesc = ddesc.left( kk );
4156  ddmap[ medtid ] = ddesc;
4157  }
4158  }
4159 DbgLv(1) << "ScMd:scan time(3)" << timer.elapsed();
4160 
4161  // Do one more pass through all the models, completing
4162  // the model descriptions
4163  for ( int mm = 0; mm < nmodel; mm++ )
4164  {
4165  QString mID = mmIDs [ mm ];
4166  QString mGUID = mmGUIDs[ mm ];
4167  QString mdesc = mmDescs[ mm ];
4168  QString meID = meIDs [ mm ];
4169  QString ddesc = ddmap.contains( meID ) ? ddmap[ meID ] : "";
4170  QString runid = mdesc.section( ".", 0, -3 );
4171  if ( meID == "1" )
4172  runid = "UNASSIGNED";
4173  QString odesc = runid + "\t" + mGUID + "\t" + mdesc + "\t" + ddesc;
4174  wDescrs << odesc;
4175  DbgLv(1) << "ScMd: mm meID" << mm << meID << "ddesc" << ddesc;
4176  }
4177 
4178  DbgLv(1) << "ScMd:scan time(9)" << timer.elapsed();
4179 
4180  return wDescrs;
4181 }

4487 //Load rawData/editedData
4488 bool US_ReporterGMP::loadData( QMap < QString, QString > & triple_information )
4489 {
4490  rawData.clear();
4491  editedData.clear();
4492 
4493  US_Passwd pw;
4494  US_DB2* db = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
4495 
4496  if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
4497  {
4498  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
4499  QMessageBox::information( this,
4500  tr( "DB Connection Problem" ),
4501  tr( "There was an error connecting to the database:\n" )
4502  + db->lastError() );
4503 
4504  return false;
4505  }
4506 
4507  qDebug() << "In load Data: triple, eID (from modelsLink) -- "
4508  << triple_information[ "triple_name" ]
4509  << Triple_to_ModelsDesc[ triple_information[ "triple_name" ] ] [ "eID" ] ;
4510 
4511  int rID=0;
4512  QString rfilename;
4513  //int eID=0;
4514  int eID = Triple_to_ModelsDesc[ triple_information[ "triple_name" ] ] [ "eID" ].toInt();
4515 
4516  QString efilename;
4517 
4518  //get EditedData filename && editedDataID for current triple, then infer rawDataID
4519  QStringList query;
4520  query << "get_editedDataFilenamesIDs_forReport" << triple_information["filename"] << QString::number( eID ) ;
4521  db->query( query );
4522 
4523  qDebug() << "In loadData() Query: " << query;
4524  qDebug() << "In loadData() Query: triple_information[ \"triple_name\" ] -- " << triple_information[ "triple_name" ];
4525 
4526  int latest_update_time = 1e100;
4527 
4528  QString triple_name_actual = triple_information[ "triple_name" ];
4529 
4530  if ( triple_name_actual.contains("Interference") )
4531  triple_name_actual.replace( "Interference", "660" );
4532 
4533  while ( db->next() )
4534  {
4535  QString filename = db->value( 0 ).toString();

4756 //Load Noises
4757 bool US_ReporterGMP::loadNoises( QMap < QString, QString > & triple_information )
4758 {
4759  US_Passwd pw;
4760  US_DB2* db = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
4761 
4762  if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
4763  {
4764  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
4765  QMessageBox::information( this,
4766  tr( "DB Connection Problem" ),
4767  tr( "There was an error connecting to the database:\n" )
4768  + db->lastError() );
4769 
4770  return false;
4771  }
4772 
4773  // get noiseIDs, types & lastUpd by modelID
4774  QStringList query;
4775  query << "get_noiseTypesIDs" << triple_information[ "mID" ];
4776  db->query( query );
4777 
4778  qDebug() << "In loadNoises() Query: " << query;
4779 
4780  int latest_update_time_ti = 1e100;
4781  int latest_update_time_ri = 1e100;
4782  int nID_ti=0;
4783  int nID_ri=0;
4784 
4785  while ( db->next() )
4786  {
4787  int noiseID = db->value( 0 ).toInt();
4788  QString noiseType = db->value( 1 ).toString();
4789  //QString date = US_Util::toUTCDatetimeText( db->value( 2 ).toDateTime().toString( "yyyy/MM/dd HH:mm" ), true );
4790  QDateTime date = db->value( 2 ).toDateTime();
4791 
4792  QDateTime now = QDateTime::currentDateTime();
4793 
4794  qDebug() << "Noises: noiseID, noiseType, date -- " << noiseID << noiseType << date;
4795 
4796  if ( noiseType.contains( "ti_" ) )
4797  {
4798  int time_to_now = date.secsTo(now);
4799  if ( time_to_now < latest_update_time_ti )
4800  {
4801  latest_update_time_ti = time_to_now;
4802 
4803  nID_ti = noiseID;
4804  }
4805  }
4806  if ( noiseType.contains( "ri_" ) )
4807  {
4808  int time_to_now = date.secsTo(now);
4809  if ( time_to_now < latest_update_time_ri )
4810  {
4811  latest_update_time_ri = time_to_now;
4812 
4813  nID_ri = noiseID;
4814  }
4815  }
4816  }
4817 
4818 
4819 
4820  //ALEXEY: treat the case when model (like -MC does not possess its own noises -- use latest available noises for prior model like -IT )
4821  //int US_LoadableNoise::count_noise() in ../../gui/us_loadable_noise.cpp
4822  //void US_FeMatch::load_noise( ) in us_fematch.cpp
4823  if ( !nID_ti && !nID_ri )
4824  loadNoises_whenAbsent();
4825 
4826  //creare US_noise objects
4827  if ( nID_ti )
4828  {
4829  ti_noise.load( QString::number( nID_ti ), db );
4830  qDebug() << "loadNoises() NORMAL: ti_noise created: ID -- " << nID_ti;
4831  }
4832  if ( nID_ri )
4833  {
4834  ri_noise.load( QString::number( nID_ri ), db );
4835  qDebug() << "loadNoises() NORMAL: ri_noise created: ID -- " << nID_ri;
4836  }
4837 
4838  // noise loaded: insure that counts jive with data
4839  int ntinois = ti_noise.values.size();
4840  int nrinois = ri_noise.values.size();
4841  int nscans = edata->scanCount();
4842  int npoints = edata->pointCount();
4843  int npadded = 0;
4844 
4845 
4846  qDebug() << "ti_noise.count, ri_noise.count: " << ti_noise.count << ri_noise.count;
4847  qDebug() << "ti_noise.values.size(), ri_noise.values.size(): " << ti_noise.values.size() << ri_noise.values.size();
4848 
4849  if ( ntinois > 0 && ntinois < npoints )
4850  { // pad out ti noise values to radius count
4851  int jj = ntinois;
4852  while ( jj++ < npoints )
4853  ti_noise.values << 0.0;
4854  ti_noise.count = ti_noise.values.size();
4855  npadded++;
4856  }
4857 
4858  if ( nrinois > 0 && nrinois < nscans )
4859  { // pad out ri noise values to scan count
4860  int jj = nrinois;
4861  while ( jj++ < nscans )
4862  ri_noise.values << 0.0;
4863  ri_noise.count = ri_noise.values.size();
4864  npadded++;
4865  }
4866 
4867  if ( npadded > 0 )
4868  { // let user know that padding occurred
4869  QString pmsg;
4870 
4871  if ( npadded == 1 )
4872  pmsg = tr( "The noise file was padded out with zeroes\n"
4873  "in order to match the data range." );
4874  else
4875  pmsg = tr( "The noise files were padded out with zeroes\n"
4876  "in order to match the data ranges." );
4877 
4878  QMessageBox::information( this, tr( "Noise Padded Out" ), pmsg );
4879  }
4880 
4881  //test:
4882  delete db;
4883  return true;
4884 }

4963 // Determine if edit/model related noise available and build lists
4964 int US_ReporterGMP::count_noise_auto( US_DataIO::EditedData* edata,
4965  US_Model* model, QStringList& mieGUIDs, QStringList& nieGUIDs )
4966 {
4967  int noidiag = US_Settings::noise_dialog();
4968 
4969  int nenois = 0; // number of edited-data-related noises
4970 
4971  if ( edata == NULL )
4972  return nenois;
4973 
4974  QStringList nimGUIDs; // list of GUIDs:type:index of noises-in-models
4975  QStringList tmpGUIDs; // temporary noises-in-model list
4976  QString daEditGUID = edata->editGUID; // loaded edit GUID
4977  QString modelGUID = ( model == 0 ) ? // loaded model GUID
4978  "" : model->modelGUID;
4979  QString lmodlGUID; // list model GUID
4980  QString lnoisGUID; // list noise GUID
4981  QString modelIndx; // "0001" style model index
4982 
4983  id_list_db_auto ( daEditGUID );
4984 
4985  // Get a list of models-with-noise tied to the loaded edit
4986  int nemods = models_in_edit_auto ( daEditGUID, mieGUIDs );
4987 
4988  if ( nemods == 0 )
4989  {
4990  //QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
4991  return nemods; // Go no further if no models-with-noise for edit
4992  }
4993 
4994  int latemx = 0; // Index to latest model-in-edit
4995 
4996  // If no model is loaded, pick the model GUID of the latest noise
4997  if ( model == 0 )
4998  modelGUID = mieGUIDs[ latemx ];
4999 
5000  // Get a list of noises tied to the loaded model
5001  int nmnois = noises_in_model_auto( modelGUID, nimGUIDs );
5002 
5003  // If the loaded model has no noise, try the latest model
5004  if ( nmnois == 0 )
5005  {
5006  modelGUID = mieGUIDs[ latemx ];
5007  nmnois = noises_in_model_auto( modelGUID, nimGUIDs );
5008  }
5009 
5010  // Insure that the loaded/latest model heads the model-in-edit list
5011  if ( modelGUID != mieGUIDs[ 0 ] )
5012  {
5013  if ( ! mieGUIDs.removeOne( modelGUID ) )
5014  {
5015  qDebug( "*ERROR* Loaded/Latest model not in model-in-edit list!" );
5016  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
5017  return 0;
5018  }
5019 
5020  mieGUIDs.insert( 0, modelGUID );
5021  }
5022 
5023 
5024  int kk = 0; // running output models index
5025 
5026  if ( nmnois > 0 )
5027  { // If loaded model has noise, put noise in list
5028  nieGUIDs << nimGUIDs; // initialize noise-in-edit list
5029  kk++;
5030  }
5031 
5032  nenois = nmnois; // initial noise-in-edit count is noises in model
5033 
5034  for ( int ii = 1; ii < nemods; ii++ )
5035  { // Search through models in edit
5036  lmodlGUID = mieGUIDs[ ii ]; // this model's GUID
5037  modelIndx = QString().sprintf( "%4.4d", kk ); // models-in-edit index
5038 
5039  // Find the noises tied to this model
5040  int kenois = noises_in_model_auto( lmodlGUID, tmpGUIDs );
5041 
5042  if ( kenois > 0 )
5043  { // if we have 1 or 2 noises, add to noise-in-edit list
5044  nenois += qMin( 2, kenois );
5045  // adjust entry to have the right model-in-edit index
5046  lnoisGUID = tmpGUIDs.at( 0 ).section( ":", 0, 1 )
5047  + ":" + modelIndx;
5048  nieGUIDs << lnoisGUID;
5049  if ( kenois > 1 )
5050  { // add a second noise to the list
5051  lnoisGUID = tmpGUIDs.at( 1 ).section( ":", 0, 1 )
5052  + ":" + modelIndx;
5053  nieGUIDs << lnoisGUID;
5054  }
5055 
5056  kk++;
5057  }
5058  }
5059 
5060 
5061  if ( nenois > 0 )
5062  { // There is/are noise(s): ask user if she wants to load
5063  QMessageBox msgBox;
5064  QString amsg;
5065  QString msg;
5066 
5067  if ( model == 0 )
5068  amsg = tr( ", associated with the loaded edit.\n" );
5069 
5070  else
5071  amsg = tr( ", associated with the loaded edit/model.\n" );
5072 
5073  if ( nenois > 1 )
5074  {
5075  msg = tr( "There are noise files" ) + amsg
5076  + tr( "Do you want to load some of them?" );
5077  }
5078 
5079  else
5080  { // Single noise file: check its value range versus experiment
5081  QString noiID = nieGUIDs.at( 0 ).section( ":", 0, 0 );
5082  US_Noise i_noise;
5083 
5084  US_Passwd pw;
5085  US_DB2 db( pw.getPasswd() );
5086  i_noise.load( true, noiID, &db );
5087 
5088  double datmin = edata->value( 0, 0 );
5089  double datmax = datmin;
5090  double noimin = 1.0e10;
5091  double noimax = -noimin;
5092  int npoint = edata->pointCount();
5093 
5094  for ( int ii = 0; ii < edata->scanData.size(); ii++ )
5095  {
5096  for ( int jj = 0; jj < npoint; jj++ )
5097  {
5098  double datval = edata->value( ii, jj );
5099  datmin = qMin( datmin, datval );
5100  datmax = qMax( datmax, datval );
5101  }
5102  }
5103 
5104  for ( int ii = 0; ii < i_noise.values.size(); ii++ )
5105  {
5106  double noival = i_noise.values[ ii ];
5107  noimin = qMin( noimin, noival );
5108  noimax = qMax( noimax, noival );
5109  }
5110 
5111  if ( ( noimax - noimin ) > ( datmax - datmin ) )
5112  { // Insert a warning if noise appears corrupt or unusual
5113  amsg = amsg
5114  + tr( "\nBUT THE NOISE HAS AN UNUSUALLY LARGE DATA RANGE.\n\n" );
5115  }
5116 
5117  msg = tr( "There is a noise file" ) + amsg
5118  + tr( "Do you want to load it?" );
5119  }
5120 
5121 DbgLv(2) << "LaNoi:noidiag " << noidiag;
5122  if ( noidiag > 0 )
5123  {
5124  msgBox.setWindowTitle( tr( "Edit/Model Associated Noise" ) );
5125  msgBox.setText( msg );
5126  msgBox.setStandardButtons( QMessageBox::No | QMessageBox::Yes );
5127  msgBox.setDefaultButton( QMessageBox::Yes );
5128 
5129  if ( msgBox.exec() != QMessageBox::Yes )
5130  { // user did not say "yes": return zero count
5131  nenois = 0; // number of edited-data-related noises
5132  }
5133  }
5134 
5135  if ( kk < nemods )
5136  { // Models with noise were found, so truncate models list
5137  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ( nemods - kk ); ii++ )
5138  mieGUIDs.removeLast();
5139  }
5140  }
5141 
5142  return nenois;
5143 }

5194 // Build lists of noise and model IDs for database
5195 int US_ReporterGMP::id_list_db_auto( QString daEditGUID )
5196 {
5197  QStringList query;
5198 
5199  US_Passwd pw;
5200  US_DB2 db( pw.getPasswd() );
5201 
5202  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
5203  return 0;
5204 
5205  query.clear();
5206  query << "get_editID" << daEditGUID;
5207  db.query( query );
5208  db.next();
5209  QString daEditID = db.value( 0 ).toString();
5210 DbgLv(1) << "LaNoi:idlDB: daEdit ID GUID" << daEditID << daEditGUID;
5211 
5212  noiIDs .clear();
5213  noiEdIDs.clear();
5214  noiMoIDs.clear();
5215  noiTypes.clear();
5216  modIDs .clear();
5217  modEdIDs.clear();
5218  modDescs.clear();
5219 
5220  QStringList reqIDs;
5221  QString noiEdID;
5222 
5223  // Build noise, edit, model ID lists for all noises
5224  query.clear();
5225  query << "get_noise_desc_by_editID" << QString::number( invID ) << daEditID;
5226  db.query( query );
5227 
5228  while ( db.next() )
5229  { // Accumulate lists from noise records
5230  noiEdID = db.value( 2 ).toString();
5231 
5232  noiIDs << db.value( 1 ).toString();
5233  noiTypes << db.value( 4 ).toString();
5234  noiMoIDs << db.value( 5 ).toString();
5235  }
5236 
5237 DbgLv(1) << "LaNoi:idlDB: noiTypes size" << noiTypes.size();
5238  // Build model, edit ID lists for all models
5239  query.clear();
5240  query << "get_model_desc_by_editID" << QString::number( invID ) << daEditID;
5241  db.query( query );
5242 
5243  while ( db.next() )
5244  { // Accumulate from db desc entries matching noise model IDs
5245  QString modGUID = db.value( 1 ).toString();
5246  QString modEdID = db.value( 6 ).toString();
5247 
5248  if ( noiMoIDs.contains( modGUID ) && modEdID == daEditID )
5249  { // Only list models that have associated noise and match edit
5250  modIDs << modGUID;
5251  modDescs << db.value( 2 ).toString();
5252  modEdIDs << db.value( 5 ).toString();
5253  }
5254  }
5255 DbgLv(1) << "LaNoi:idlDB: modDescs size" << modDescs.size();
5256 
5257  // Loop through models to edit out any extra monteCarlo models
5258  for ( int ii = modIDs.size() - 1; ii >=0; ii-- )
5259  { // Work from the back so any removed records do not affect indexes
5260  QString mdesc = modDescs.at( ii );
5261  QString asysID = mdesc.section( ".", -2, -2 );
5262  bool mCarlo = ( asysID.contains( "-MC" ) &&
5263  asysID.contains( "_mc" ) );
5264  QString reqID = asysID.section( "_", 0, -2 );
5265 
5266  if ( mCarlo )
5267  { // Treat monte carlo in a special way (as single composite model)
5268  if ( reqIDs.contains( reqID ) )
5269  { // already have this request GUID, so remove this model
5270  modIDs .removeAt( ii );
5271  modDescs.removeAt( ii );
5272  modEdIDs.removeAt( ii );
5273  }
5274 
5275  else
5276  { // This is the first time for this request, so save it in a list
5277  reqIDs << reqID;
5278  }
5279  }
5280  }
5281 
5282  // Create list of edit GUIDs for noises
5283  for ( int ii = 0; ii < noiTypes.size(); ii++ )
5284  {
5285  QString moGUID = noiMoIDs.at( ii );
5286  int jj = modIDs.indexOf( moGUID );
5287 DbgLv(2) << "LaNoi:idlDB: ii jj moGUID" << ii << jj << moGUID;
5288 
5289  QString edGUID = ( jj < 0 ) ? "" : modEdIDs.at( jj );
5290 
5291  noiEdIDs << edGUID;
5292  }
5293 
5294  return noiIDs.size();
5295 }

5298 void US_ReporterGMP::simulateModel( QMap < QString, QString> & tripleInfo )

5309

5319

5322  << model.components[ 0].signal_concentration;
5323  qDebug() << "SimMdl: n) s D c"
5324  << model.components[lc].s << model.components[lc].D
5325  << model.components[lc].signal_concentration;
5326

5333  simparams.meshType = US_SimulationParameters::ASTFEM;

5336  // simparams.bottom = simparams.bottom_position;

5338  << "rreso" << simparams.radial_resolution
5339  << "bottom_sim" << simparams.bottom << "bottom_dat" << edata->bottom;
5340  //simparams.meniscus = 5.8;
5341 
5342  //sdata.scanData.resize( total_scans );
5343  //int terpsize = ( points + 7 ) / 8;
5344 
5345 
5346  //test
5347  delete dbP;
5348 
5349  if ( exp_steps )
5350  simparams.speed_step = speed_steps;
5351 
5352  qDebug() << "SimMdl: speed_steps:" << simparams.speed_step.size();
5353 
5354  QString mtyp = adv_vals[ "meshtype" ];
5355  QString gtyp = adv_vals[ "gridtype" ];
5356  QString bvol = adv_vals[ "bandvolume" ];
5357 
5358 
5359  if ( gtyp.contains( "Constant" ) )
5360  simparams.gridType = US_SimulationParameters::FIXED;
5361 
5362  if ( model.components[ 0 ].sigma == 0.0 &&
5363  model.components[ 0 ].delta == 0.0)
5364  simparams.meshType = US_SimulationParameters::ASTFEM;
5365  else
5366  simparams.meshType = US_SimulationParameters::ASTFVM;
5367

5374  simparams.band_volume = bvol.toDouble();
5375  //concval1 = 1.0;
5376  //simparams.firstScanIsConcentration = true;
5377  }
5378  else
5379  simparams.band_volume = 0.0;
5380 
5381  // Make a simulation copy of the experimental data without actual readings
5382 
5383  qDebug() << "SimulateModel: --- 1";
5384 
5385  US_AstfemMath::initSimData( *sdata, *edata, concval1 );// Gets experimental time grid set
5386 
5387  qDebug() << "SimulateModel: --- 2";
5388 
5389 
5390  QString tmst_fpath = US_Settings::resultDir() + "/" + FileName_parsed + "/"
5391  + FileName_parsed + ".time_state.tmst";
5392  QFileInfo check_file( tmst_fpath );
5393  simparams.sim = ( edata->channel == "S" );
5394 
5395  if ( ( check_file.exists() ) && ( check_file.isFile() ) )
5396  {
5397  if ( US_AstfemMath::timestate_onesec( tmst_fpath, *sdata ) )
5398  { // Load timestate that is already at 1-second-intervals
5399  simparams.simSpeedsFromTimeState( tmst_fpath );
5400  qDebug() << "SimMdl: timestate file exists" << tmst_fpath << " timestateobject,count = "
5401  << simparams.tsobj << simparams.sim_speed_prof.count();
5402  simparams.speedstepsFromSSprof();
5403  }
5404 
5405  else
5406  { // Replace timestate with a new one that is at 1-second-intervals
5407  // if ( drow == 0 )
5408  // {
5409  QString tmst_fdefs = QString( tmst_fpath ).replace( ".tmst", ".xml" );
5410  QString tmst_fpsav = tmst_fpath + "-orig";
5411  QString tmst_fdsav = tmst_fdefs + "-orig";
5412  simparams.sim = ( edata->channel == "S" );
5413 
5414  // Rename existing (non-1sec-intv) files
5415  QFile::rename( tmst_fpath, tmst_fpsav );
5416  QFile::rename( tmst_fdefs, tmst_fdsav );
5417  // Create a new 1-second-interval file set
5418  US_AstfemMath::writetimestate( tmst_fpath, simparams, *sdata );
5419  qDebug() << "SimMdl: 1-sec-intv file created";
5420  // }
5421 
5422  simparams.simSpeedsFromTimeState( tmst_fpath );
5423  simparams.speedstepsFromSSprof();
5424  }
5425  }
5426  else
5427  {
5428  qDebug() << "SimMdl: timestate file does not exist";
5429  if ( ! simparams.sim )
5430  { // Compute acceleration rate for non-astfem_sim data
5431  const double tfac = ( 4.0 / 3.0 );
5432  double t2 = simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].time_first;
5433  double w2t = simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].w2t_first;
5434  double om1t = simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].rotorspeed * M_PI / 30.0;
5435  double w2 = sq( om1t );
5436  double t1 = tfac * ( t2 - ( w2t / w2 ) );
5437  int t_acc = (int)qRound( t1 );
5438  double rate = (double)( simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].rotorspeed )
5439  / (double)t_acc;
5440  qDebug() << "SimMdl: accel-calc: t1 t2 w2t t_acc speed rate"
5441  << t1 << t2 << w2t << t_acc << simparams.speed_step[0].rotorspeed << rate;
5442  simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].acceleration = (int)qRound( rate );
5443  }
5444  }
5445 
5446  // Do a quick test of the speed step implied by TimeState
5447  int tf_scan = simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].time_first;
5448  int accel1 = simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].acceleration;
5449  QString svalu = US_Settings::debug_value( "SetSpeedLowA" );
5450  int lo_ss_acc = svalu.isEmpty() ? 250 : svalu.toInt();
5451  int rspeed = simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].rotorspeed;
5452  double tf_aend = static_cast<double>(tf_scan);
5453  // prevent any division by zero
5454  if (accel1 != 0)
5455  {
5456  tf_aend = static_cast<double>(rspeed) / static_cast<double>(accel1);
5457  }
5458 
5459  qDebug() << "SimMdl: ssck: rspeed accel1 lo_ss_acc"
5460  << rspeed << accel1 << lo_ss_acc << "tf_aend tf_scan"
5461  << tf_aend << tf_scan;
5462  //x0 1 2 3 4 5
5463  // check if the acceleration rate is low or the first scan was taken before the acceleration ended
5464  // Due to older, wrong timestate calculation there might be a case, in which the calculated end of acceleration can
5465  // be up to 1 second later than expected, tf_scan + 1 accounts for this.
5466  if ( accel1 < lo_ss_acc || tf_aend > ( tf_scan + 1 ) )
5467  {
5468  QString wmsg = tr( "The TimeState computed/used is likely bad:<br/>"
5469  "The acceleration implied is %1 rpm/sec.<br/>"
5470  "The acceleration zone ends at %2 seconds,<br/>"
5471  "with a first scan time of %3 seconds.<br/><br/>"
5472  "<b>You should rerun the experiment without<br/>"
5473  "any interim constant speed, and then<br/>"
5474  "you should reimport the data.</b>" )
5475  .arg( accel1 ).arg( QString::number(tf_aend) ).arg( QString::number(tf_scan) );
5476 
5477  QMessageBox msgBox( this );
5478  msgBox.setWindowTitle( tr( "Bad TimeState Implied!" ) );
5479  msgBox.setTextFormat( Qt::RichText );
5480  msgBox.setText( wmsg );
5481  msgBox.addButton( tr( "Continue" ), QMessageBox::RejectRole );
5482  QPushButton* bAbort = msgBox.addButton( tr( "Abort" ),
5483  QMessageBox::YesRole );
5484  msgBox.setDefaultButton( bAbort );
5485  msgBox.exec();
5486  if ( msgBox.clickedButton() == bAbort )
5487  {
5488  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
5489  qApp->processEvents();
5490  return;
5491  }
5492  }
5493  sdata->cell = rdata->cell;
5494  sdata->channel = rdata->channel;
5495  sdata->description = rdata->description;
5496 
5497  if ( dbg_level > 0 )
5498  simparams.save_simparms( US_Settings::etcDir() + "/sp_fematch.xml" );
5499 
5500  //start_time = QDateTime::currentDateTime();
5501  int ncomp = model.components.size();
5502  //compress = le_compress->text().toDouble();
5503  progress_msg->setRange( 1, ncomp );
5504  // progress_msg->reset();
5505 
5506  nthread = US_Settings::threads();
5507  int ntc = ( ncomp + nthread - 1 ) / nthread;
5508  nthread = ( ntc > MIN_NTC ) ? nthread : 1;
5509 
5510  /*
5511  //TEST
5512  nthread = 10;
5513  */
5514 
5515  qDebug() << "SimMdl: nthread" << nthread << "ncomp" << ncomp
5516  << "ntc" << ntc << "meshtype" << simparams.meshType;
5517 
5518  // Do simulation by several possible ways: 1-/Multi-thread, ASTFEM/ASTFVM
5519  //if ( nthread < 2 )
5520  if ( nthread < 999 )
5521  {
5522  if ( model.components[ 0 ].sigma == 0.0 &&
5523  model.components[ 0 ].delta == 0.0 &&
5524  model.coSedSolute < 0.0 &&
5525  compress == 0.0 )
5526  {
5527  qDebug() << "SimMdl: (fematch:)Finite Element Solver is called";
5528  //*DEBUG*
5529  for(int ii=0; ii<model.components.size(); ii++ )
5530  {
5531  qDebug() << "SimMdl: comp" << ii << "s D v"
5532  << model.components[ii].s
5533  << model.components[ii].D
5534  << model.components[ii].vbar20 << " c"
5535  << model.components[ii].signal_concentration;
5536  }
5537  qDebug() << "SimMdl: (fematch:)Sim Pars--";
5538  simparams.debug();
5539  //*DEBUG*
5540  US_Astfem_RSA* astfem_rsa = new US_Astfem_RSA( model, simparams );
5541 
5542  connect( astfem_rsa, SIGNAL( current_component( int ) ),
5543  this, SLOT ( update_progress ( int ) ) );
5544  astfem_rsa->set_debug_flag( dbg_level );
5545  solution_rec.buffer.compressibility = compress;
5546  solution_rec.buffer.manual = manual;
5547  //astfem_rsa->set_buffer( solution_rec.buffer );
5548 
5549  astfem_rsa->calculate( *sdata );
5550  //*DEBUG*
5551  int kpts=0;
5552  double trmsd=0.0;
5553  double tnoi=0.0;
5554  double rnoi=0.0;
5555  bool ftin=ti_noise.count > 0;
5556  bool frin=ri_noise.count > 0;
5557  for(int ss=0; ss<sdata->scanCount(); ss++)
5558  {
5559  rnoi = frin ? ri_noise.values[ss] : 0.0;
5560  for (int rr=0; rr<sdata->pointCount(); rr++)
5561  {
5562  tnoi = ftin ? ti_noise.values[rr] : 0.0;
5563  double rval=edata->value(ss,rr) - sdata->value(ss,rr) - rnoi - tnoi;
5564  trmsd += sq( rval );
5565  kpts++;
5566  }
5567  }
5568  trmsd = sqrt( trmsd / (float)kpts );
5569  qDebug() << "SimMdl: (1)trmsd" << trmsd;
5570  //*DEBUG*
5571  }
5572  else
5573  {
5574  qDebug() << "SimMdl: (fematch:)Finite Volume Solver is called";
5575  US_LammAstfvm *astfvm = new US_LammAstfvm( model, simparams );
5576  astfvm->calculate( *sdata );
5577  }
5578  //-----------------------
5579  //Simulation part is over
5580  //-----------------------
5581 
5582  show_results( triple_info_map );
5583  }
5584 
5585  else
5586  { // Do multi-thread calculations
5587 
5588  qDebug() << "Simulate Model: Multi-thread -- ";
5589 
5590  solution_rec.buffer.compressibility = compress;
5591  solution_rec.buffer.manual = manual;
5592  tsimdats.clear();
5593  tmodels .clear();
5594  kcomps .clear();
5595  QList< ThreadWorker* > tworkers;
5596  QList< QThreadEx* > wthreads;
5597 
5598  // Build models for each thread
5599  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ncomp; ii++ )
5600  {
5601  if ( ii < nthread )
5602  { // First time through per thread: get initial model and sim data
5603  tmodels << model;
5604  tmodels[ ii ].components.clear();
5605  US_DataIO::RawData sdat = *sdata;
5606  tsimdats << sdat;
5607  kcomps << 0;
5608  }
5609 
5610  // Partition thread models from round-robin fetch of components
5611  int jj = ii % nthread;
5612  tmodels[ jj ].components << model.components[ ii ];
5613  }
5614 
5615  thrdone = 0;
5616  solution_rec.buffer.manual = manual;
5617 
5618  // Build worker threads and begin running
5619  for ( int ii = 0; ii < nthread; ii++ )
5620  {
5621  ThreadWorker* tworker = new ThreadWorker( tmodels[ ii ], simparams,
5622  tsimdats[ ii ], solution_rec.buffer, ii );
5623  QThreadEx* wthread = new QThreadEx();
5624 
5625  tworker->moveToThread( wthread );
5626 
5627  tworkers << tworker;
5628  wthreads << wthread;
5629 
5630  connect( wthread, SIGNAL( started() ),
5631  tworker, SLOT ( calc_simulation() ) );
5632 
5633  connect( tworker, SIGNAL( work_progress ( int, int ) ),
5634  this, SLOT( thread_progress( int, int ) ) );
5635  connect( tworker, SIGNAL( work_complete ( int ) ),
5636  this, SLOT( thread_complete( int ) ) );
5637 
5638  wthread->start();
5639  }
5640  }
5641 }

5684 //Check if model exists for particular stage (2DSA-IT, or 2DSA-MC...) by its modelGUID (across all triples)
5685 bool US_ReporterGMP::modelGuidExistsForStage( QString model, QString mguid)
5686 {
5687  bool isModelGuid = false;
5688 
5689  for ( int i=0; i < Array_of_tripleNames.size(); ++ i )
5690  {
5691  QMap< QString, QString > tmapguid = Triple_to_ModelsDescGuid[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ];
5692 
5693  if ( tmapguid[ model ] == mguid )
5694  {
5695  qDebug() << "For stage: " << model << ", there is modelGuid: " << mguid << " (" << Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] << ")";
5696 
5697  isModelGuid = true;
5698  break;
5699  }
5700  }
5701 
5702  return isModelGuid;
5703 }

5706 //[IND] Check if model exists for particular stage (2DSA-IT, or 2DSA-MC...) by its modelGUID (for specified triple)
5707 bool US_ReporterGMP::modelGuidExistsForStage_ind( QString triple_n, QString model, QString mguid)
5708 {
5709  bool isModelGuid = false;
5710 
5711  for ( int i=0; i < Array_of_tripleNames.size(); ++ i )
5712  {
5713  QString c_triple_n = Array_of_tripleNames[ i ];
5714  c_triple_n. replace(".","");
5715 
5716  qDebug() << "IN modelGuidExistsForStage_ind(): triple_n, c_triple_n, model -- "
5717  << triple_n << c_triple_n << model;
5718  qDebug() << "IN modelGuidExistsForStage_ind(): mguid, Triple_to_ModelsDescGuid[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ][ model ] -- "
5719  << mguid << Triple_to_ModelsDescGuid[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ][ model ];
5720 
5721  if ( c_triple_n == triple_n )
5722  {
5723  QMap< QString, QString > tmapguid = Triple_to_ModelsDescGuid[ Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] ];
5724 
5725  if ( tmapguid[ model ] == mguid )
5726  {
5727  qDebug() << "For triple, stage: " << triple_n << model << ", there is modelGuid: " << mguid << " (" << Array_of_tripleNames[ i ] << ")";
5728 
5729  isModelGuid = true;
5730  break;
5731  }
5732  }
5733  }
5734 
5735  return isModelGuid;
5736 }

5964 //pull s_ranges, k_ranges from AProfile
5965 QMap< QString, QStringList > US_ReporterGMP::find_sim_ranges( QString chann_desc, QString model )
5966 {
5967  QMap < QString, QStringList > sim_ranges;
5968 
5969  qDebug() << "[in find_sim_ranges()1] -- " << chann_desc << model;
5970 
5971  if ( model. contains("2DSA") )
5972  {
5973  //2DSA
5974  for (int i=0; i<cAP2.parms.size(); ++i )
5975  {
5976  QString channame = cAP2.parms[i].channel;
5977  qDebug() << "[2DSA]channame -- " << channame;
5978 
5979  if ( channame. contains( chann_desc ) )
5980  {
5981  sim_ranges[ "s_ranges" ] << QString::number( cAP2.parms[i].s_min )
5982  << QString::number( cAP2.parms[i].s_max );
5983  sim_ranges[ "k_ranges" ] << QString::number( cAP2.parms[i].k_min )
5984  << QString::number( cAP2.parms[i].k_max );
5985  break;
5986  }
5987  }
5988  }
5989  else if ( model. contains("PCSA") )
5990  {
5991  //PCSA
5992  for (int i=0; i<cAPp.parms.size(); ++i )
5993  {
5994  QString channame = cAPp.parms[i].channel;
5995  qDebug() << "[PCSA]channame -- " << channame;
5996 
5997  if ( channame. contains( chann_desc ) )
5998  {
5999  sim_ranges[ "s_ranges" ] << QString::number( cAPp.parms[i].x_min )
6000  << QString::number( cAPp.parms[i].x_max );
6001  sim_ranges[ "y_ranges" ] << QString::number( cAPp.parms[i].y_min )
6002  << QString::number( cAPp.parms[i].y_max );
6003  break;
6004  }
6005  }
6006  }
6007 
6008  return sim_ranges;
6009 }

6013 {

6309 
6310 // Calculate residual absorbance values (data - sim - noise)
6311 void US_ReporterGMP::calc_residuals()
6312 {
6313  int dsize = edata->pointCount();
6314  int ssize = sdata->pointCount();
6315  QVector< double > vecxx( dsize );
6316  QVector< double > vecsx( ssize );
6317  QVector< double > vecsy( ssize );
6318  double* xx = vecxx.data();
6319  double* sx = vecsx.data();
6320  double* sy = vecsy.data();
6321  double yval;
6322  double sval;
6323  double rmsd = 0.0;
6324  double tnoi = 0.0;
6325  double rnoi = 0.0;
6326  bool ftin = ti_noise.count > 0;
6327  bool frin = ri_noise.count > 0;
6328  bool matchd = ( dsize == ssize );
6329  int kpts = 0;
6330  qDebug() << "CALC_RESID: matchd" << matchd << "dsize ssize" << dsize << ssize;
6331  int kexcls=0;
6332 
6333  QVector< double > resscan;
6334 
6335  resids .clear();
6336  resscan.resize( dsize );
6337 
6338  for ( int jj = 0; jj < dsize; jj++ )
6339  {
6340  xx[ jj ] = edata->radius( jj );
6341  }
6342 
6343  for ( int jj = 0; jj < ssize; jj++ )
6344  {
6345  sx[ jj ] = sdata->radius( jj );
6346  if ( sx[ jj ] != xx[ jj ] ) matchd = false;
6347  }
6348 
6349  for ( int ii = 0; ii < scanCount; ii++ )
6350  {
6351  bool usescan = !excludedScans.contains( ii );
6352 if(!usescan) kexcls++;
6353 
6354  rnoi = frin ? ri_noise.values[ ii ] : 0.0;
6355 
6356  for ( int jj = 0; jj < ssize; jj++ )
6357  {
6358  sy[ jj ] = sdata->value( ii, jj );
6359  }
6360 
6361  for ( int jj = 0; jj < dsize; jj++ )
6362  { // Calculate the residuals and the RMSD
6363  tnoi = ftin ? ti_noise.values[ jj ] : 0.0;
6364 
6365  if ( matchd )
6366  sval = sy[ jj ];
6367  else
6368  sval = interp_sval( xx[ jj ], sx, sy, ssize );
6369 
6370  yval = edata->value( ii, jj ) - sval - rnoi - tnoi;
6371 
6372  if ( usescan )
6373  {
6374  rmsd += sq( yval );
6375  kpts++;
6376  }
6377 
6378  resscan[ jj ] = yval;
6379  }
6380 
6381  resids << resscan;
6382  }
6383 
6384  rmsd /= (double)( kpts );
6385  //le_variance->setText( QString::number( rmsd ) );
6386  rmsd = sqrt( rmsd );
6387 
6388  rmsd_global = QString::number( rmsd );
6389 
6390  qDebug() << "CALC_RESID: matchd" << matchd << "kexcls" << kexcls << "rmsd" << rmsd;
6391 
6392 }

6499  {
6500  QTextStream tso( &fileo );
6501  tso << xdefs;
6502  tso.flush();
6503  fileo.close();
6504  qDebug() << "Assembling Run Details: xdefs WRITTEN";
6505  }
6506 
6507 
6508  //6. Get access to Timestamp info, possibly plots also...
6509  // Point to any existing time state file

6520

6522  { // Looks like we have a TMST and corresponding Defs XML
6523  tmst_fnamei = tmsfs[ 0 ];
6524  defs_fnamei = tmsfs[ 1 ];

6530  tmst_fnamei = tmst_dname + tmst_fnamei;
6531  }
6532

6534  tmsfs[ 1 ].contains( ".tmst" ) )
6535  { // Have both files (in opposite order), so save full path to TMST

6587  double val_measured_stdd = 0;

6595  << currProto. rpSpeed. ssteps[0].speed
6596  << currProto. rpSpeed. ssteps[0].accel;
6597  int hours_r = (int)qFloor( val_target / 3600.0 );
6598  int mins_r = (int)qRound( ( val_target - hours_r * 3600.0 ) / 60.0 );
6599  QString hh_r = "h";
6600  QString val_target_hh_mm = QString().sprintf( "%d %s %02d m", hours_r, hh_r.toLatin1().data(), mins_r );
6601

6604  QString channel_desc = chndescs[ 0 ];

6606  US_ReportGMP reportGMP = ch_reports[ channel_desc_alt ][ wvl ];
6607  val_tol = reportGMP. experiment_duration_tol;
6608 
6609  val_measured = dmaxs[ dkeys[ i ] ] - dmins[ dkeys[ i ] ]; //in mins
6610  double val_measured_sec = val_measured * 60.0;
6611  hours_r = (int)qFloor( val_measured_sec / 3600.0 );
6612  mins_r = (int)qRound( ( val_measured_sec - hours_r * 3600.0 ) / 60.0 );
6613  QString val_measured_hh_mm = QString().sprintf( "%d %s %02d m", hours_r, hh_r.toLatin1().data(), mins_r );
6614 
6615  val_passed = ( val_measured_sec >= ( val_target * (1 - val_tol/100.0) ) && val_measured_sec <= ( val_target * (1 + val_tol/100.0) ) ) ? "YES" : "NO";
6616 
6617  html_assembled += table_row( tr( "Duration" ),
6618  val_target_hh_mm,

6621  "",
6622  val_passed ) ;
6623  }
6624

6626  if ( dkeys[ i ] .contains("Temperature") )
6627  {

6629  val_target = currProto.temperature;
6630  val_measured = davgs_stdd_first_scan [ dkeys[ i ] ][ "Avg" ];
6631  val_passed = ( val_measured >= ( val_target - val_tol ) && val_measured <= ( val_target + val_tol ) ) ? "YES" : "NO";
6632 
6633  val_measured_stdd = davgs_stdd_first_scan [ dkeys[ i ] ][ "Stdd" ];
6634

6636  QString::number( val_target ),

6647  }
6648 
6649  //RawSpeed
6650  if ( dkeys[ i ] .contains("RawSpeed") )
6651  {
6652  val_tol = 4; //plus-minus 4 RPM
6653  val_target = currProto. rpSpeed. ssteps[0].speed;
6654  val_measured = davgs_stdd_first_scan [ dkeys[ i ] ][ "Avg" ];
6655  val_passed = ( val_measured >= ( val_target - val_tol ) && val_measured <= ( val_target + val_tol ) ) ? "YES" : "NO";
6656 
6657  html_assembled += table_row( "Speed (RPM)",
6658  QString::number( val_target ),
6659  "&#177;" + QString::number( val_tol ),
6660  QString::number( val_measured ),
6661  "",

6668  RunDetailsPlotsFileNames << img01File;
6669  }

6699 //get expID
6700 int US_ReporterGMP::get_expID_by_runID_invID( US_DB2* dbP, QString runID_filename )
6701 {
6702  QStringList query;
6703  int idExp = 0;
6704  query << "get_experiment_info_by_runID"
6705  << runID_filename
6706  << QString::number(invID);
6707  qDebug() << "get_experiment_info_by_runID: qry -- " << query;
6708  dbP->query( query );
6709 
6710  if ( dbP->lastErrno() == US_DB2::OK )
6711  {
6712  dbP->next();
6713  idExp = dbP->value( 1 ).toInt();
6714  }
6715 
6716  return idExp;
6717 }

7423 //Read AProfile's reportIDs per channel:
7424 void US_ReporterGMP::read_reportLists_from_aprofile( QStringList & dropped_triples_RI, QStringList & dropped_triples_IP )
7425 {
7426  dropped_triples_RI. clear();
7427  dropped_triples_IP. clear();
7428  QMap< QString, QString> channame_to_reportIDs_RI;
7429  QMap< QString, QString> channame_to_reportIDs_IP;
7430  QString aprofile_xml;
7431 
7432  // Check DB connection
7433  US_Passwd pw;
7434  QString masterPW = pw.getPasswd();
7435  US_DB2 db( masterPW );
7436 
7437  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
7438  {
7439  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
7440  tr( "Read protocol: Could not connect to database \n" ) + db.lastError() );
7441  return;
7442  }
7443 
7444  qDebug() << "AProfGUID: " << AProfileGUID;
7445 
7446  QStringList qry;
7447  qry << "get_aprofile_info" << AProfileGUID;
7448  db.query( qry );
7449 
7450  while ( db.next() )
7451  {
7452  aprofile_xml = db.value( 2 ).toString();
7453  }
7454 
7455  if ( !aprofile_xml.isEmpty() )
7456  {
7457  QXmlStreamReader xmli( aprofile_xml );
7458  readReportLists( xmli, channame_to_reportIDs_RI, channame_to_reportIDs_IP );
7459  }
7460 
7461  //Now, construct list of dropped triples per optical system used:
7462  dropped_triples_RI = buildDroppedTriplesList( &db, channame_to_reportIDs_RI );
7463  dropped_triples_IP = buildDroppedTriplesList( &db, channame_to_reportIDs_IP );
7464 }

7466 //Build list of dropped triples out of channame_to_reportIDs QMap;
7467 QStringList US_ReporterGMP::buildDroppedTriplesList ( US_DB2* dbP, QMap <QString, QString> channame_to_reportIDs )
7468 {
7469  QStringList dropped_triples_list;
7470 
7471  QMap<QString, QString>::iterator chan_rep;
7472  for ( chan_rep = channame_to_reportIDs.begin(); chan_rep != channame_to_reportIDs.end(); ++chan_rep )
7473  {
7474  QString chan_key = chan_rep.key();
7475  QString reportIDs = chan_rep.value();
7476  qDebug() << "Channel name -- " << chan_key << ", reportIDs -- " << reportIDs;
7477 
7478  QStringList reportIDs_list = reportIDs.split(",");
7479  for (int i=0; i<reportIDs_list.size(); ++i)
7480  {
7481  QString rID = reportIDs_list[i];
7482  QString Wavelength;
7483  QString TripleDropped;
7484 
7485  QStringList qry;
7486  qry << "get_report_info_by_id" << rID;
7487  dbP->query( qry );
7488 
7489  if ( dbP->lastErrno() == US_DB2::OK )
7490  {
7491  while ( dbP->next() )
7492  {
7493  Wavelength = dbP->value( 5 ).toString();
7494  TripleDropped = dbP->value( 9 ).toString();
7495  }
7496 
7497  if ( TripleDropped == "YES" )
7498  {
7499  QString dropped_triple_name = chan_key + "." + Wavelength;
7500  dropped_triples_list << dropped_triple_name;
7501  }
7502  }
7503  }
7504  }
7505 
7506  return dropped_triples_list;
7507 }
7508 
7509 //Read AProfile's reportIDs per channel:
7510 bool US_ReporterGMP::readReportLists( QXmlStreamReader& xmli, QMap< QString, QString> & channame_to_reportIDs_RI, QMap< QString, QString> & channame_to_reportIDs_IP )
7511 {
7512  while( ! xmli.atEnd() )
7513  {
7514  QString ename = xmli.name().toString();
7515 
7516  if ( xmli.isStartElement() )
7517  {
7518  if ( ename == "channel_parms" )
7519  {
7520  QXmlStreamAttributes attr = xmli.attributes();
7521 
7522  if ( attr.hasAttribute("load_volume") ) //ensure it reads upper-level <channel_parms>
7523  {
7524  QString channel_name = attr.value( "channel" ).toString();
7525  QString channel_desc = attr.value( "chandesc" ).toString();
7526 
7527  QString opsys = channel_desc.split(":")[1]; // UV/vis. or Interf.
7528 
7529  if ( opsys.contains("UV/vis") ) //RI
7530  {
7531  //Read what reportID corresponds to channel:
7532  if ( attr.hasAttribute("report_id") )
7533  channame_to_reportIDs_RI[ channel_name ] = attr.value( "report_id" ).toString();
7534  }
7535  if ( opsys.contains("Interf") ) //IP
7536  {
7537  //Read what reportID corresponds to channel:
7538  if ( attr.hasAttribute("report_id") )
7539  channame_to_reportIDs_IP[ channel_name ] = attr.value( "report_id" ).toString();
7540  }
7541  }
7542  }
7543  }
7544 
7545  bool was_end = xmli.isEndElement(); // Just read was End of element?
7546  xmli.readNext(); // Read the next element
7547 
7548  if ( was_end && ename == "p_2dsa" ) // Break
7549  break;
7550  }
7551 
7552  return ( ! xmli.hasError() );
7553 }

7635 //Parse autoflowStatus Analysis Json
7636 QMap < QString, QString > US_ReporterGMP::parse_autoflowStatus_analysis_json( QString statusJson )
7637 {
7638  QMap <QString, QString> status_map;
7639 
7640  QJsonDocument jsonDoc = QJsonDocument::fromJson( statusJson.toUtf8() );
7641 
7642  if ( jsonDoc. isArray() )
7643  {
7644  QJsonArray json_array = jsonDoc.array();
7645  qDebug() << "IN ANALYSIS_JSON [ARRAY]: " << json_array;
7646 
7647  for (int i=0; i < json_array.size(); ++i )
7648  {
7649  foreach(const QString& key, json_array[ i ].toObject().keys())
7650  {
7651  QJsonValue value = json_array[ i ].toObject().value(key);
7652  qDebug() << "ANALYSIS_JSON [ARRAY]: key, value: " << key << value.toString();
7653 
7654  status_map[ key ] = value.toString();
7655  }
7656  }
7657  }
7658  else if ( jsonDoc. isObject() )
7659  {
7660  QJsonObject json_obj = jsonDoc.object();
7661  qDebug() << "IN ANALYSIS_JSON [OBJECT]: " << json_obj;
7662 
7663  foreach(const QString& key, json_obj.keys())
7664  {
7665  QJsonValue value = json_obj.value(key);
7666  qDebug() << "ANALYSIS_JSON [OBJECT]: key, value: " << key << value;
7667 
7668  status_map[ key ] = value.toString();
7669  }
7670  }
7671 
7672  return status_map;
7673 }
7674 
7675 //Parse autoflowStatus RI/IP Json
7676 QMap< QString, QMap < QString, QString > > US_ReporterGMP::parse_autoflowStatus_json( QString statusJson, QString dtype )
7677 {
7678  QMap< QString, QMap <QString, QString> > status_map;
7679 
7680  QJsonDocument jsonDoc = QJsonDocument::fromJson( statusJson.toUtf8() );
7681  QJsonObject json_obj = jsonDoc.object();
7682 
7683  foreach(const QString& key, json_obj.keys())
7684  {
7685  QJsonValue value = json_obj.value(key);
7686 
7687  qDebug() << "statusJson key, value: " << key << value;
7688 
7689  if ( key == "Person" ) //GMP init || live_update || import || edit
7690  {
7691  QJsonArray json_array = value.toArray();
7692  QMap< QString, QString > person_map;
7693 
7694  for (int i=0; i < json_array.size(); ++i )
7695  {
7696  foreach(const QString& array_key, json_array[i].toObject().keys())
7697  {
7698  person_map[ array_key ] = json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
7699  qDebug() << "Person Map: -- key, value: "
7700  << array_key
7701  << json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
7702  }
7703  }
7704 
7705  status_map[ key ] = person_map;
7706  }
7707 
7708  if ( key == "RefScan" ) //import: Ref. scan
7709  {
7710  status_map[ key ][ "type" ] = value.toString();
7711  }
7712 
7713  //Comment when SAVED:
7714  if ( key == "Comment when SAVED" ) //import || edit
7715  {
7716  status_map[ key ][ "comment_when_saved" ] = value.toString();
7717  }
7718 
7719 
7720  if ( key == "Dropped" ) // import: Dropped triples/channels/select channels operaitons
7721  {
7722  QJsonArray json_array = value.toArray();
7723  QMap< QString, QString > dropped_map;
7724 
7725  for (int i=0; i < json_array.size(); ++i )
7726  {
7727  foreach(const QString& array_key, json_array[i].toObject().keys())
7728  {
7729  dropped_map[ array_key ] = json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
7730  qDebug() << "Dropped Map: -- key, value: "
7731  << array_key
7732  << json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
7733  }
7734  }
7735 
7736  status_map[ key ] = dropped_map;
7737  }
7738 
7739 
7740  if ( key == "Meniscus" ) //edit
7741  {
7742  QJsonArray json_array = value.toArray();
7743  QMap< QString, QString > meniscus_map;
7744 
7745  for (int i=0; i < json_array.size(); ++i )
7746  {
7747  foreach(const QString& array_key, json_array[i].toObject().keys())
7748  {
7749  meniscus_map[ array_key ] = json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
7750  qDebug() << "Meniscus Map: -- key, value: "
7751  << array_key
7752  << json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
7753  }
7754  }
7755 
7756  status_map[ key ] = meniscus_map;
7757  }
7758 
7759  if ( key == "Remote Operation" ) //Live Update's remote operations [SKIP | STOP]
7760  {
7761  status_map[ key ][ "type" ] = value.toString();
7762  }
7763  if ( key == "Comment" ) //GMP init || Live Update's remote operations [SKIP | STOP]
7764  {
7765  status_map[ key ][ "comment" ] = value.toString();
7766  }
7767 
7768  }
7769 
7770  return status_map;
7771 }

7796 QString US_ReporterGMP::distrib_info_abde( QString& abde_channame )
7797 {
7798  //TimeStamps
7799  QString mstr = "\n" + indent( 2 )
7800  + tr( "<h3>Timestamps:</h3>\n" )
7801  + indent( 2 ) + "<table>\n";
7802  mstr += table_row( tr( "Data Edited at:" ), editing_time_abde + " (UTC)");
7803  mstr += table_row( tr( "Analysed at:" ), analysis_time_abde + " (UTC)");
7804  mstr += indent( 2 ) + "</table>\n";
7805 
7806  //if MWL-Deconv., add info on which analytes' ext. profiles have been used
7807  bool mwl_abde = false;
7808  for ( int ii = 0; ii < currProto.rpRange. nranges; ii++ )
7809  {
7810  if ( currProto.rpRange. chrngs[ii].wvlens.size() > 1 )
7811  {
7812  mwl_abde = true;
7813  break;
7814  }
7815  }
7816  if( mwl_abde )
7817  {
7818  mstr += "\n" + indent( 2 )
7819  + tr( "<h3>Analytes and Buffer Used in MWL-Deconvolution:</h3>\n" )
7820  + indent( 2 ) + "<table>\n";
7821  QMap< QString, QString > channs_analytes_buffers = get_channels_analytes_mwl_abde( abde_channame );
7822 
7823  QMap < QString, QString >::iterator ab;
7824  for ( ab = channs_analytes_buffers.begin(); ab != channs_analytes_buffers.end(); ++ab )
7825  mstr += table_row( ab.key(), ab.value() );
7826 
7827  mstr += indent( 2 ) + "</table>\n";
7828 
7829  //Main Analysis Settings
7830  mstr += "\n" + indent( 2 )
7831  + tr( "<h3>Data Analysis Settings:</h3>\n" )
7832  + indent( 2 ) + "<table>\n";
7833 
7834  mstr += table_row( tr( "Residual RMS Deviation:" ),
7835  QString::number( abde_rmsd[abde_channame] ) );
7836  mstr += indent( 2 ) + "</table>\n";
7837  }
7838 
7839  //Distribution Info - to separate .pdf file //////////////////////////////////////////////////
7840  mstr += "\n" + indent( 2 ) + tr( "<h3>Distribution Information:</h3>\n" );
7841  mstr += indent( 2 ) + "<table>\n";
7842 
7843  QString subDirName = runName + "-run" + runID;
7844  QString dirName = US_Settings::reportDir() + "/" + subDirName;
7845  mkdir( US_Settings::reportDir(), subDirName );
7846 
7847  QString abde_dist_info;
7848  QString html_abde_s;
7849 
7850  if ( mwl_abde )
