7987 
7988  // reportGMP-> reportItems[ kk ]. integration_val_sim = int_val_m;
7989  // reportGMP-> reportItems[ kk ]. total_percent_sim = frac_tot_m;
7990  // reportGMP-> reportItems[ kk ]. passed = tot_frac_passed;
7991 
7992  qDebug() << "In distrib_info(), fill simulated integration vals: for chann/wvl/type/method/low/high, "

7996  << curr_item.method
7997  << curr_item.range_low
7998  << curr_item.range_high
7999  << int_val_m;
8000 
8001  mstr += table_row( type,
8002  range,
8003  QString().sprintf( "%5.2f%%", frac_tot_m ) + " (" + QString::number( frac_tot_r ) + "%)",
8004  QString::number( frac_tot_tol_r ),
8005  tot_frac_passed );
8006  }
8007  mstr += indent( 2 ) + "</table>\n";

8009  }
8010 
8011  return mstr;
8012 }

8014 //ABDE: read all analytes (& possibly buffers) used in MWL-deconv.
8015 QMap< QString, QString > US_ReporterGMP::get_channels_analytes_mwl_abde( QString abde_channame )
8016 {
8017  QMap< QString, QString > analytes_buffer_map;
8018 
8019  US_Passwd pw;
8020  QString masterPW = pw.getPasswd();
8021  US_DB2 db( masterPW );
8022 
8023  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
8024  {
8025  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Database Problem" ),
8026  tr( "Database returned the following error: \n" ) + db.lastError() );
8027 
8028  return analytes_buffer_map;
8029  }
8030 
8031  for ( int ii = 0; ii < currProto.rpRange.nranges; ii++ )
8032  {
8033  QString channel = currProto.rpRange.chrngs[ ii ].channel;
8034  QString channel_s = channel.split(",")[0].trimmed();
8035  channel_s.replace(" / ","");
8036  qDebug() << "[in get_channels_analytes_mwl_abde()], channel, channel_s, abde_channame;"
8037  << channel << channel_s << abde_channame;
8038 
8039  if ( channel_s == abde_channame )
8040  {
8041  QList< double > all_wvls = currProto.rpRange.chrngs[ ii ].wvlens;
8042  int nwavl = all_wvls.count();
8043  bool buff_req = currProto.rpRange.chrngs[ ii ].abde_buffer_spectrum;
8044  bool mwl_deconv = currProto.rpRange.chrngs[ ii ].abde_mwl_deconvolution;
8045 
8046  if ( nwavl > 1 && mwl_deconv )
8047  {
8048  QString sol_id = currProto.rpSolut.chsols[ii].sol_id;
8049  US_Solution* solution = new US_Solution;
8050  int solutionID = sol_id.toInt();
8051 
8052  int status = US_DB2::OK;
8053  status = solution->readFromDB ( solutionID, &db );
8054  // Error reporting
8055  if ( status == US_DB2::NO_BUFFER )
8056  {
8057  QMessageBox::information( this,
8058  tr( "Attention" ),
8059  tr( "The buffer this solution refers to was not found.\n"
8060  "Please restore and try again.\n" ) );
8061  return analytes_buffer_map;
8062  }
8063 
8064  else if ( status == US_DB2::NO_ANALYTE )
8065  {
8066  QMessageBox::information( this,
8067  tr( "Attention" ),
8068  tr( "One of the analytes this solution refers to was not found.\n"
8069  "Please restore and try again.\n" ) );
8070  return analytes_buffer_map;
8071  }
8072 
8073  else if ( status != US_DB2::OK )
8074  {
8075  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Database Problem" ),
8076  tr( "Database returned the following error: \n" ) + db.lastError() );
8077  return analytes_buffer_map;
8078  }
8079  //End of reading Solution:
8080 
8081  //Reading Analytes
8082  int num_analytes = solution->analyteInfo.size();
8083  for (int i=0; i < num_analytes; ++i )
8084  {
8085  US_Analyte analyte = solution->analyteInfo[ i ].analyte;
8086  QString a_name = analyte.description;
8087  QString a_ID = analyte.analyteID;
8088  QString a_GUID = analyte.analyteGUID;
8089 
8090  qDebug() << "[GMP REPORT] Solution " << solution->solutionDesc
8091  << ", (GUID)Analyte " << "(" << a_GUID << ")" << a_name
8092  << ", (ID)Analyte " << "(" << a_ID << ")" << a_name;
8093 
8094  QString ana_name = "Analyte #" + QString::number(i+1) + ":";
8095  analytes_buffer_map[ ana_name ] = a_name;
8096  }
8097 
8098  //Reading Buffers
8099  if ( buff_req ) //only if buffer spectrum required
8100  {
8101  US_Buffer buffer = solution->buffer;
8102  QString b_name = buffer.description;
8103  QString b_ID = buffer.bufferID;
8104  qDebug() << "[GMP REPORT] Solution " << solution->solutionDesc
8105  << ", (ID)Buffer " << "(" << b_ID << ")" << b_name;
8106 
8107  analytes_buffer_map[ "Buffer:" ] = b_name;
8108  }
8109  }
8110  }
8111  }
8112 
8113  return analytes_buffer_map;
8114 }

8242 // Interpolate an sdata y (readings) value for a given x (radius)
8243 double US_ReporterGMP::interp_sval( double xv, double* sx, double* sy, int ssize )
8244 {
8245  for ( int jj = 1; jj < ssize; jj++ )
8246  {
8247  if ( xv == sx[ jj ] )
8248  {
8249  return sy[ jj ];
8250  }
8251 
8252  if ( xv < sx[ jj ] )
8253  { // given x lower than array x: interpolate between point and previous
8254  int ii = jj - 1;
8255  double dx = sx[ jj ] - sx[ ii ];
8256  double dy = sy[ jj ] - sy[ ii ];
8257  return ( sy[ ii ] + ( xv - sx[ ii ] ) * dy / dx );
8258  }
8259  }
8260 
8261  // given x position not found: interpolate using last two points
8262  int jj = ssize - 1;
8263  int ii = jj - 1;
8264  double dx = sx[ jj ] - sx[ ii ];
8265  double dy = sy[ jj ] - sy[ ii ];
8266  return ( sy[ ii ] + ( xv - sx[ ii ] ) * dy / dx );
8267 }

8269 // Model type text string
8270 QString US_ReporterGMP::text_model( US_Model model, int width )
8271 {
8272  QString stitle = model.typeText();
8273  QString title = stitle;
8274  QString m_desc = model. description;
8275 
8276  if ( width != 0 )
8277  { // long title: add any suffixes and check need to center
8278  switch ( (int)model.analysis )
8279  {
8280  case (int)US_Model::TWODSA:
8281  case (int)US_Model::TWODSA_MW:
8282  title = tr( "2-Dimensional Spectrum Analysis" );
8283 
8284  if ( m_desc. contains("-IT") )
8285  title = title + " (IT)";
8286 
8287  break;
8288 
8289  case (int)US_Model::GA:
8290  case (int)US_Model::GA_MW:
8291  title = tr( "Genetic Algorithm Analysis" );
8292  break;
8293 
8294  case (int)US_Model::COFS:
8295  title = tr( "C(s) Analysis" );
8296  break;
8297 
8298  case (int)US_Model::FE:
8299  title = tr( "Finite Element Analysis" );
8300  break;
8301 
8302  case (int)US_Model::PCSA:
8303  title = tr( "Parametrically Constrained Spectrum Analysis\n" );
8304 
8305  if ( stitle.contains( "-SL" ) )
8306  title += tr( "(Straight Line)" );
8307 
8308  else if ( stitle.contains( "-IS" ) )
8309  title += tr( "(Increasing Sigmoid)" );
8310 
8311  else if ( stitle.contains( "-DS" ) )
8312  title += tr( "(Decreasing Sigmoid)" );
8313 
8314  else if ( stitle.contains( "-HL" ) )
8315  title += tr( "(Horizontal Line)" );
8316 
8317  else if ( stitle.contains( "-2O" ) )
8318  title += tr( "(2nd-Order Power Law)" );
8319 
8320  break;
8321 
8322  case (int)US_Model::DMGA:
8323  title = tr( "Discrete Model Genetic Algorithm" );
8324  break;
8325 
8326  case (int)US_Model::MANUAL:
8327  default:
8328  title = tr( "2-Dimensional Spectrum Analysis" );
8329  break;
8330  }
8331 
8332 
8333  if ( stitle.contains( "-SL" ) )
8334  if ( model.associations.size() > 1 )
8335  title = title + " (RA)";
8336 
8337  if ( model.global == US_Model::MENISCUS )
8338  title = title + " (Menisc.)";
8339 
8340  else if ( model.global == US_Model::GLOBAL )
8341  title = title + " (Global)";
8342 
8343  else if ( model.global == US_Model::SUPERGLOBAL )
8344  title = title + " (S.Glob.)";
8345 
8346  if ( model.monteCarlo )
8347  title = title + " (MC)";
8348 
8349  if ( width > title.length() )
8350  { // long title centered: center it in fixed-length string
8351  int lent = title.length();
8352  int lenl = ( width - lent ) / 2;
8353  int lenr = width - lent - lenl;
8354  title = QString( " " ).repeated( lenl ) + title
8355  + QString( " " ).repeated( lenr );
8356  }
8357  }
8358 
8359  return title;
8360 }

8452 // Calculate and output Averages from Replicate groups
8453 QString US_ReporterGMP::calc_replicates_averages( void )
8454 {
8455  /*
8456  Replicate group #1: [channels 1A, 5A, 6A]
8457  Subgroup 1: ----- Same: wvl, type/method, ranges, integraiton value
8458  triples: 1A.280, 5A.280, 6A.280 (overlapping wvls)
8459  type/method: [s / 2DSA-IT]
8460  ranges: [3.2 - 3.7]
8461  integration value: 0.57
8462 
8463  Subgroup 2: ----- Same: wvl, type/method, ranges, integraiton value
8464  triples: 1A.280, 5A.280, 6A.280 (overlapping wvls)
8465  type/method: [s / 2DSA-MC]
8466  ranges: [3.4 - 3.9]
8467  integration value: 0.51
8468 
8469  Subgroup 3: ----- Same: wvl, type/method, ranges, integraiton value
8470  triples: 1A.320, 5A.320, 6A.320 (overlapping wvls)
8471  type/method: [D / PCSA]
8472  ranges: [3.1 - 4.9]
8473  integration value: 0.59
8474 =====================================================================================
8475 
8476  Replicate group #2: [channels 2A, 4A, 6B]
8477  Subgroup 1: ----- Same: wvl, type/method, ranges, integraiton value
8478  triples: 2A.290, 6B.290 (overlapping wvls) --> IT Maybe that 4A does not have wvl 290!!!
8479  type/method: [s / 2DSA-IT]
8480  ranges: [3.2 - 3.7]
8481  integration value: 0.57
8482 
8483  Subgroup 2: ----- Same: wvl, type/method, ranges, integraiton value
8484  triples: 2A.290, 6B.290 (overlapping wvls) --> IT Maybe that 4A does not have wvl 290!!!
8485  type/method: [D / 2DSA-IT]
8486  ranges: [3.4 - 3.9]
8487  integration value: 0.51
8488 
8489 =====================================================================================
8490 
8491  Now, the 1st triple in a given subgroup (same-wvl triples) is the REFERENCE one:
8492  - e.g., 1A.280, in Replicate #1, subgroup 1,2;
8493  1A.320, in Replicate #1, subgroup 3;
8494  2A.290, in Replicate #2, subgroup 1,2;
8495 
8496  ** Retrieve US_ReportGMP for these REFERENCE triples && go over theirs ReportItems:
8497 
8498  -- US_ReportGMP ref_report = ch_reports[ channel_desc_alt ][ wvl ];
8499 
8500  channel_desc_alt && wvl are from:
8501  QMap< QString, QStringList > channdesc_to_overlapping_wvls[ channel_desc_alt ] [ QStringList( "2A.260","2B.260","4A.260","2A.275","2B.275","4A.275","2A.280","2B.280","4A.280","4B.280","6A.280","6B.280" )]
8502 
8503  IMPORTANT: in QStringList, group triples by same-wvl (subgroups), then [0] in each group will be REFERENCE wvl!
8504  So, reference triples in the above QStringList example will be:
8505  2A.260, 2A.275 && 2A.280
8506 
8507  -- Start by iterating over QMap< QString, QStringList > channdesc_to_overlapping_wvls:
8508  iterator::key() - channel_desc_at;
8509  iterator::value() - access to wvl; IMPORTANT, break into same-wvl groups, then take 1st to access wvl of the REFERNECE triple
8510 
8511  -- Iterate over ReportItems in ref_report.reportItems;
8512  -- For each unique ReportItem, identify type-method, ranges, int.value;
8513  -- Retrive earlier processed (in ::distrib_info() ) integration results for subgroup triples && AVERAGE
8514 
8515  -- BEFORE: in ::distrib_info() STORE integration results into respective reportItem[ kk ]. { integration_val_sim; ...}
8516 
8517  */
8518 
8519  QString html_str_replicate_av;
8520 
8521  if ( !channdesc_to_overlapping_wvls.isEmpty() )
8522  html_str_replicate_av += tr( "<h2>Replicate Groups Averaging Results:</h2>\n" );
8523 
8524  QMap< QString, QStringList>::iterator chw;
8525  for ( chw = channdesc_to_overlapping_wvls.begin(); chw != channdesc_to_overlapping_wvls.end(); ++chw )
8526  {
8527  QString ch_alt_desc = chw.key();
8528  QStringList all_wvls = chw.value();
8529  QString o_type = ch_alt_desc.split(":")[1];
8530 
8531  QStringList unique_wvls;
8532  QStringList unique_channels;
8533  QMap < QString, QStringList > same_wvls_chann_map; // wvl: channel list
8534 
8535  for( int i=0; i<all_wvls.size(); ++i )
8536  {
8537  QString curr_triple = all_wvls[ i ];
8538  QString curr_chann = all_wvls[ i ].split(".")[0];
8539  QString curr_wvl = all_wvls[ i ].split(".")[1];
8540 
8541  unique_wvls << curr_wvl;
8542  unique_channels << curr_chann;
8543 
8544  //here, add to list FULL channel desc, e.g. "1A:Iterf.", or "1A:UV/vis."
8545  //same_wvls_chann_map[ curr_wvl ] << curr_chann; //BEFORE
8546  same_wvls_chann_map[ curr_wvl ] << curr_chann + ":" + o_type; //Will this work?
8547  }
8548 
8549  unique_wvls. removeDuplicates();
8550  unique_channels. removeDuplicates();
8551 
8552  QString replicate_group_number = get_replicate_group_number( ch_alt_desc );
8553 
8554  html_str_replicate_av += "\n" + indent( 2 ) + tr( "<h3>Replicate Group #%1: [Channels: %2 (%3)] </h3>\n" )
8555  .arg( replicate_group_number )
8556  .arg( unique_channels.join(",") )
8557  .arg( o_type );
8558 
8559 
8560  //iterate over unique wvls
8561  for ( int j=0; j < unique_wvls.size(); ++j )
8562  {
8563  QString u_wvl = unique_wvls[j];
8564 
8565  QString replicate_subgroup_triples;
8566  for ( int jj=0; jj < same_wvls_chann_map[ u_wvl ].size(); ++jj )
8567  replicate_subgroup_triples += same_wvls_chann_map[ u_wvl ][ jj ].split(":")[0] + "." + u_wvl + ",";
8568 
8569  replicate_subgroup_triples.chop(1);
8570 
8571  html_str_replicate_av += "\n" + indent( 2 ) + tr( "<h3>Subgroup #%1: [Triples: %2] </h3>\n" )
8572  .arg( QString::number( j+1 ) )
8573  .arg( replicate_subgroup_triples );
8574 
8575  html_str_replicate_av += indent( 2 ) + "<table style=\"font-size:80%\">\n";
8576  html_str_replicate_av += table_row( tr( "Type:" ),
8577  tr( "Method:" ),
8578  tr( "Range:"),
8579  tr( "Av. Integration, Model (target):" ),
8580  tr( "St. Dev.:"),
8581  tr( "Av. Fraction %, Model (target):"),
8582  tr( "St. Dev.:" ),
8583  tr( "Tol.%:"),
8584  tr( "PASSED?")
8585  );
8586 
8587  //Reference GMP Report, ReportItems for 1st channel in a replicate group && over each wavelength:
8588  US_ReportGMP ref_group_report = ch_reports[ ch_alt_desc ][ u_wvl ];
8589  int report_items_number = ref_group_report.reportItems.size();
8590  for ( int kk = 0; kk < report_items_number; ++kk )
8591  {
8592  US_ReportGMP::ReportItem ref_group_item = ref_group_report.reportItems[ kk ];
8593 
8594  QString type = ref_group_item.type;
8595  QString method = ref_group_item.method;
8596  if( method.contains ("PCSA") )
8597  method = "PCSA";
8598  QString int_val_r = QString::number( ref_group_item.integration_val );
8599  double frac_tot_r = ref_group_item.total_percent;
8600  double frac_tot_tol_r = ref_group_item.tolerance ;
8601  double low = ref_group_item.range_low;
8602  double high = ref_group_item.range_high;
8603 
8604  QString range = "[" + QString::number(low) + " - " + QString::number(high) + "]";
8605 
8606  QMap<QString, double> replicate_g_results = get_replicate_group_results( ref_group_item, u_wvl, same_wvls_chann_map[ u_wvl ] );
8607 
8608  //print results into HTML report:
8609  /*
8610  Replicate Group #: [channles: 1A, 2A, 5A]
8611  Sub-Group #: [wvl: 280]
8612  type, method, range, integration_AV (target), St.Dev. Fraction of Total AV. (target) PASSED?
8613  s 2DSA-MC 3.2-3.7 integration_sim_av st_dev XXX YES/NO
8614  */
8615 
8616  double frac_tot_m_av = replicate_g_results["tot_percent_av"];
8617  QString tot_av_frac_passed = ( frac_tot_m_av >= ( frac_tot_r * (1 - frac_tot_tol_r/100.0) )
8618  && frac_tot_m_av <= ( frac_tot_r * (1 + frac_tot_tol_r/100.0) ) ) ? "YES" : "NO";
8619 
8620  html_str_replicate_av += table_row( type,
8621  method,
8622  range,
8623  QString().sprintf( "%10.4e", replicate_g_results["int_av"] ) + " (" + int_val_r + ")",
8624  QString().sprintf( "%10.2e", replicate_g_results["int_st_dev"] ),
8625  QString().sprintf( "%5.2f%%", replicate_g_results["tot_percent_av"] ) +
8626  " (" + QString().sprintf( "%5.2f%%", frac_tot_r) + ")",
8627  QString().sprintf( "%5.2f%%", replicate_g_results["tot_percent_st_dev"] ),
8628  QString::number( frac_tot_tol_r ),
8629  tot_av_frac_passed
8630  );
8631  }
8632 
8633  html_str_replicate_av += indent( 3 ) + "</table>\n";
8634  }
8635  }
8636 
8637  return html_str_replicate_av;
8638 }

8658 //Get Integration Results from same Replicate subGroup | same-wvl | same-report-items:
8659 QMap<QString, double> US_ReporterGMP::get_replicate_group_results( US_ReportGMP::ReportItem ref_report_item, QString u_wvl, QStringList channs_for_wvl )
8660 {
8661  double int_res_sim = 0;
8662  double int_res_sim_av = 0;
8663  double tot_percent_sim = 0;
8664  double tot_percent_sim_av = 0;
8665 
8666  int same_item_counter = 0;
8667  double st_dev_int_1 = 0;
8668  double st_dev_int_final = 0;
8669  double st_dev_tot_percent_1 = 0;
8670  double st_dev_tot_percent_final = 0;
8671  QVector< double > int_res_sim_vector;
8672  QVector< double > tot_percent_sim_vector;
8673 
8674  QMap< QString, double > results;
8675 
8676  //iterate over UR_ReportsGMPs && pick ones correspondning to 'chan_desc_alt.contains("ch_wvls[i]")' && wavelength == u_wvl;
8677  int nchna = currAProf.pchans.count();
8678  for ( int i = 0; i < channs_for_wvl.size(); ++i ) //over channels for a given wvl in Replicate group:
8679  {
8680  US_ReportGMP reportGMP;
8681  for ( int j = 0; j < nchna; j++ ) //over all channels
8682  {
8683  QString channel_desc_alt = chndescs_alt[ j ];
8684 
8685  // //For now, do not consider IP type!!!
8686  // if ( channel_desc_alt.contains("Interf") )
8687  // continue;
8688 
8689  //if ( channel_desc_alt.split(":")[0].contains( channs_for_wvl[ i ] ) )
8690  if ( channel_desc_alt .contains( channs_for_wvl[ i ] ) )
8691  {
8692  qDebug() << "In get_replicate_group_results(): channel_desc_alt, channs_for_wvl[ i ], wvl -- "
8693  << channel_desc_alt
8694  << channs_for_wvl[ i ]
8695  << u_wvl;
8696 
8697  //Select US_ReportGMP for channel in a Replicate group && representative wvl!
8698  reportGMP = ch_reports[ channel_desc_alt ][ u_wvl ];
8699 
8700  break;
8701  }
8702  }
8703 
8704  //then pick report's ReportItem corresponding to the passed ref_report_item:
8705  int report_items_number = reportGMP. reportItems.size();
8706  for ( int kk = 0; kk < report_items_number; ++kk )
8707  {
8708  US_ReportGMP::ReportItem curr_item = reportGMP. reportItems[ kk ];
8709 
8710  //Compare ref_report_item with curr_item:
8711  QString ref_type = ref_report_item.type;
8712  QString ref_method = ref_report_item.method;
8713  QString ref_int_val = QString::number( ref_report_item.integration_val );
8714  double ref_frac_tot = ref_report_item.total_percent;
8715  double ref_frac_tot_tol = ref_report_item.tolerance ;
8716  double ref_low = ref_report_item.range_low;
8717  double ref_high = ref_report_item.range_high;
8718 
8719  QString _type = curr_item.type;
8720  QString _method = curr_item.method;
8721  QString _int_val = QString::number( curr_item.integration_val );
8722  double _frac_tot = curr_item.total_percent;
8723  double _frac_tot_tol = curr_item.tolerance ;
8724  double _low = curr_item.range_low;
8725  double _high = curr_item.range_high;
8726 
8727  //Comparison nased on: type/method [s-2DSA-IT], ranges [3.2 - 3.7] && integration value: CAN BE EXTENDED if needed
8728  if ( ref_type == _type &&
8729  ref_method == _method &&
8730  ref_low == _low &&
8731  ref_high == _high &&
8732  ref_int_val == _int_val )
8733  {
8734 
8735  //can add an average fraction percent from model (if needed)
8736 
8737  qDebug() << "For Triple: " << channs_for_wvl[ i ] << "." << u_wvl
8738  << ", Type/Method: " << _type << ": " << _method
8739  << ", Range: " << "[" << _low << " - " << _high << "]"
8740  << ", Simulated Integr. Val: " << curr_item. integration_val_sim
8741  << ", Fraction %: " << curr_item. total_percent_sim;
8742 
8743  if ( curr_item. integration_val_sim >= 0 )
8744  {
8745  int_res_sim += curr_item. integration_val_sim;
8746  tot_percent_sim += curr_item. total_percent_sim;
8747  int_res_sim_vector .push_back( curr_item. integration_val_sim );
8748  tot_percent_sim_vector .push_back( curr_item. total_percent_sim );
8749 
8750  ++same_item_counter;
8751  }
8752  }
8753  }
8754  }
8755 
8756  if ( same_item_counter )
8757  {
8758  int_res_sim_av = double( int_res_sim / same_item_counter );
8759  tot_percent_sim_av = double( tot_percent_sim / same_item_counter );
8760 
8761  for( int i=0; i<int_res_sim_vector.size(); ++i )
8762  {
8763  st_dev_int_1 += ( int_res_sim_av - int_res_sim_vector[i] ) * ( int_res_sim_av - int_res_sim_vector[i] );
8764  st_dev_tot_percent_1 += ( tot_percent_sim_av - tot_percent_sim_vector[i] ) * ( tot_percent_sim_av - tot_percent_sim_vector[i] );
8765  }
8766 
8767  st_dev_int_final = sqrt( st_dev_int_1 ) / (sqrt( int_res_sim_vector.size() ));
8768  st_dev_tot_percent_final = sqrt( st_dev_tot_percent_1 ) / (sqrt( tot_percent_sim_vector.size() ));
8769  }
8770 
8771  results[ "int_av" ] = int_res_sim_av;
8772  results[ "tot_percent_av" ] = tot_percent_sim_av;
8773  results[ "int_st_dev" ] = st_dev_int_final;
8774  results[ "tot_percent_st_dev" ] = st_dev_tot_percent_final;
8775 
8776 
8777  return results;
8778 }
8779 
8780 // Distribution information HTML string
8781 QString US_ReporterGMP::distrib_info( QMap < QString, QString> & tripleInfo )
8782 {
8783  int ncomp = model_used.components.size();
8784  double vari_m = model_used.variance;
8785  double rmsd_m = ( vari_m == 0.0 ) ? 0.0 : sqrt( vari_m );
8786 
8787  qDebug() << "Distrib_info(): Model Name, time created, editUpdated -- "
8788  << model.description
8789  << model.timeCreated
8790  << model.editDataUpdated;
8791 
8792  if ( ncomp == 0 )
8793  return "";
8794 
8795  QString msim = adv_vals[ "modelsim" ];
8796 
8797  if ( is_dmga_mc )
8798  {
8799 
8800  if ( msim == "model" )
8801  { // Use DMGA-MC single-iteration model
8802  msim = "<b>&nbsp;&nbsp;( single iteration )</b>";
8803  }
8804  else
8805  { // Use mean|median|mode model
8806  msim = "<b>&nbsp;&nbsp;( " + msim + " )</b>";
8807  }
8808  }
8809  else
8810  { // Normal non-DMGA-MC model
8811  msim = "";
8812  if ( model_used.monteCarlo &&
8813  ! model_used.description.contains( "_mcN" ) )
8814  msim = "<b>&nbsp;&nbsp;( single iteration )</b>";
8815  }
8816 
8817  QString mdla = model_used.description
8818  .section( ".", -2, -2 ).section( "_", 1, -1 );
8819  if ( mdla.isEmpty() )
8820  mdla = model_used.description.section( ".", 0, -2 );
8821 
8822 
8823  //TimeStamps
8824  QString mstr = "\n" + indent( 2 )
8825  + tr( "<h3>Timestamps:</h3>\n" )
8826  + indent( 2 ) + "<table>\n";
8827  mstr += table_row( tr( "Data Edited at:" ), model.editDataUpdated + " (UTC)");
8828  mstr += table_row( tr( "Model Analysed at:" ), model.timeCreated + " (UTC)");
8829  mstr += indent( 2 ) + "</table>\n";
8830 
8831 
8832  mstr += "\n" + indent( 2 )
8833  + tr( "<h3>Data Analysis Settings:</h3>\n" )
8834  + indent( 2 ) + "<table>\n";
8835 
8836  mstr += table_row( tr( "Model Analysis:" ), mdla + msim );
8837  mstr += table_row( tr( "Number of Components:" ),
8838  QString::number( ncomp ) );
8839  mstr += table_row( tr( "Residual RMS Deviation:" ),
8840  rmsd_global );
8841  mstr += table_row( tr( "Model-reported RMSD:" ),
8842  ( rmsd_m > 0.0 ) ? QString::number( rmsd_m ) : "(none)" );
8843 
8844  double sum_mw = 0.0;
8845  double sum_s = 0.0;
8846  double sum_D = 0.0;
8847  double sum_c = 0.0;
8848  double sum_v = 0.0;
8849  double sum_k = 0.0;
8850  double mink = 1e+99;
8851  double maxk = -1e+99;
8852  double minv = 1e+99;
8853  double maxv = -1e+99;
8854 
8855  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ncomp; ii++ )
8856  {
8857  double conc = model_used.components[ ii ].signal_concentration;
8858  double kval = model_used.components[ ii ].f_f0;
8859  double vval = model_used.components[ ii ].vbar20;
8860  sum_c += conc;
8861  sum_mw += ( model_used.components[ ii ].mw * conc );
8862  sum_s += ( model_used.components[ ii ].s * conc );
8863  sum_D += ( model_used.components[ ii ].D * conc );
8864  sum_v += ( vval * conc );
8865  sum_k += ( kval * conc );
8866  mink = qMin( kval, mink );
8867  maxk = qMax( kval, maxk );
8868  minv = qMin( vval, minv );
8869  maxv = qMax( vval, maxv );
8870  }
8871 
8872  mstr += table_row( tr( "Weight Average s20,W:" ),

9743 
9744 double US_ReporterGMP::get_loading_volume( int cellID )
9745 {
9746  double vol = 0;
9747 
9748  double speed = currProto. rpSpeed. ssteps[0].speed ;
9749  double stretch = simparams.rotorcoeffs[ 0 ] * speed + simparams.rotorcoeffs[ 1 ] * sq( speed ) ;
9750 
9751  qDebug() << "Centerpeice: stretch: " << stretch;
9752 
9753 
9754  //get centerpiece info
9755  QString centerpiece_name = "";
9756  for ( int i=0; i < currProto. rpCells. used. size(); ++i )
9757  {
9758  if ( currProto. rpCells. used [ i ]. cell == cellID )
9759  {
9760  centerpiece_name = currProto. rpCells. used [ i ]. centerpiece;
9761  qDebug() << "In get_loading_volume(): cell, cenerpiece -- "
9762  << currProto. rpCells. used [ i ]. cell
9763  << currProto. rpCells. used [ i ]. centerpiece ;
9764 
9765  break;
9766  }
9767  }
9768 
9769  // Check DB connection
9770  US_Passwd pw;
9771  QString masterPW = pw.getPasswd();
9772  US_DB2 db( masterPW );
9773 
9774  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
9775  {
9776  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
9777  tr( "Read protocol: Could not connect to database \n" ) + db.lastError() );
9778  return vol;
9779  }
9780 
9781  //Find centerpieceID on DB based on centerpiece name:
9782  QString centerpieceID_read;
9783  QStringList query;
9784  query.clear();
9785  query << "get_abstractCenterpiece_names";
9786  db.query( query );
9787 
9788  while ( db.next() )
9789  {
9790  QString id = db.value( 0 ).toString();
9791  QString name = db.value( 1 ).toString();
9792 
9793  if ( centerpiece_name == name )
9794  {
9795  centerpieceID_read = id;
9796  break;
9797  }
9798  }
9799 
9800  if ( centerpieceID_read.isEmpty() )
9801  {
9802  qDebug() << "In get_loading_volume(): Couldn't read centerpiece name ! ";
9803 
9804  return vol;
9805  }
9806 
9807  //Now, get centerpiece info
9808  query.clear();
9809  query << "get_abstractCenterpiece_info" << centerpieceID_read;
9810  db.query( query );
9811  db.next();
9812 
9813  QString c_name = db.value( 1 ).toString();
9814  double c_bottom = db.value( 3 ).toString().toDouble();
9815  double c_pathlength = db.value( 6 ).toString().toDouble();
9816  double c_angle = db.value( 7 ).toString().toDouble();
9817 
9818  qDebug() << "In get_loading_volume(): c_name, c_bottom, c_pathlength, c_angle -- "
9819  << c_name << c_bottom << c_pathlength << c_angle;
9820 
9821  //add stretching
9822  c_bottom += stretch;
9823 
9824  //meniscus position
9825  double meniscus = model_used. meniscus;
9826  qDebug() << "In get_loading_volume(): meniscus -- " << meniscus;
9827 
9828  //calulate loading volume
9829  vol = ( c_bottom*c_bottom - meniscus*meniscus ) * ( 1000*c_pathlength*c_angle*M_PI ) / 360.0;
9830 
9831  return vol;
9832 }

10094 
10095 // Do stick type distribution plot
10096 void US_ReporterGMP::distrib_plot_stick( int type )
10097 {
10098  QString pltitle = tr( "Run " ) + edata->runID + tr( " :\nCell " )
10099  + edata->cell + " (" + edata->wavelength + " nm)";
10100  QString xatitle;
10101  QString yatitle = tr( "Rel. Concentr." );
10102 
10103  if ( type == 0 )
10104  {
10105  pltitle = pltitle + tr( "\ns20,W Distribution" );
10106  xatitle = tr( "Corrected Sedimentation Coefficient" );
10107  }
10108 
10109  else if ( type == 1 )
10110  {
10111  pltitle = pltitle + tr( "\nMW Distribution" );
10112  xatitle = tr( "Molecular Weight (Dalton)" );
10113  }
10114 
10115  else if ( type == 2 )
10116  {
10117  pltitle = pltitle + tr( "\nD20,W Distribution" );
10118  xatitle = tr( "D20,W (cm^2/sec)" );
10119  }
10120 
10121  dataPlotClear( data_plot1 );
10122 
10123  data_plot1->setTitle( pltitle );
10124  data_plot1->setAxisTitle( QwtPlot::yLeft, yatitle );
10125  data_plot1->setAxisTitle( QwtPlot::xBottom, xatitle );
10126 
10127  QwtPlotGrid* data_grid = us_grid( data_plot1 );
10128  QwtPlotCurve* data_curv = us_curve( data_plot1, "distro" );
10129 
10130 
10131  int dsize = model_used.components.size();
10132  QVector< double > vecx( dsize );
10133  QVector< double > vecy( dsize );
10134  double* xx = vecx.data();
10135  double* yy = vecy.data();
10136  double xmin = 1.0e30;
10137  double xmax = -1.0e30;
10138  double ymin = 1.0e30;
10139  double ymax = -1.0e30;
10140  double xval;
10141  double yval;
10142  double rdif;
10143 
10144  for ( int jj = 0; jj < dsize; jj++ )
10145  {
10146  xval = ( type == 0 ) ? model_used.components[ jj ].s :
10147  ( ( type == 1 ) ? model_used.components[ jj ].mw :
10148  model_used.components[ jj ].D );
10149  yval = model_used.components[ jj ].signal_concentration;
10150  xx[ jj ] = xval;
10151  yy[ jj ] = yval;
10152  xmin = min( xval, xmin );
10153  xmax = max( xval, xmax );
10154  ymin = min( yval, ymin );
10155  ymax = max( yval, ymax );
10156  }
10157 
10158  rdif = ( xmax - xmin ) / 20.0;
10159  xmin -= rdif;
10160  xmax += rdif;
10161  rdif = ( ymax - ymin ) / 20.0;
10162  ymin -= rdif;
10163  ymax += rdif;
10164  xmin = ( type == 0 ) ? xmin : max( xmin, 0.0 );
10165  ymin = max( ymin, 0.0 );
10166 
10167  data_grid->enableYMin ( true );
10168  data_grid->enableY ( true );
10169  data_grid->setMajorPen(
10170  QPen( US_GuiSettings::plotMinGrid(), 0, Qt::DotLine ) );
10171 
10172  data_curv->setSamples( xx, yy, dsize );
10173  data_curv->setPen ( QPen( Qt::yellow, 3, Qt::SolidLine ) );
10174  data_curv->setStyle ( QwtPlotCurve::Sticks );
10175 
10176  data_plot1->setAxisAutoScale( QwtPlot::xBottom );
10177  data_plot1->setAxisAutoScale( QwtPlot::yLeft );
10178  data_plot1->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::xBottom, xmin, xmax );
10179  data_plot1->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::yLeft, ymin, ymax );
10180 
10181  data_plot1->replot();
10182 }
10183 
10184 // Do 2d type distribution plot
10185 void US_ReporterGMP::distrib_plot_2d( int type )
10186 {
10187  QString pltitle = tr( "Run " ) + edata->runID + tr( " :\nCell " )
10188  + edata->cell + " (" + edata->wavelength + " nm)";
10189  QString yatitle;
10190  QString xatitle;
10191 
10192  if ( type == 3 )
10193  {
10194  pltitle = pltitle + tr( "\nf/f0 vs Sed. Coeff." );
10195  yatitle = tr( "Frictional Ratio f/f0" );
10196  xatitle = tr( "Sedimentation Coefficient s20,W" );
10197  }
10198 
10199  else if ( type == 4 )
10200  {
10201  pltitle = pltitle + tr( "\nf/f0 vs Mol. Weight" );
10202  yatitle = tr( "Frictional Ratio f/f0" );
10203  xatitle = tr( "Molecular Weight" );
10204  }
10205 
10206  else if ( type == 5 )
10207  {
10208  pltitle = pltitle + tr( "\nVbar vs Sed. Coeff." );
10209  yatitle = tr( "Vbar at 20" ) + DEGC;
10210  xatitle = tr( "Sedimentation Coefficient s20,W" );
10211  }
10212 
10213  else if ( type == 6 )
10214  {
10215  pltitle = pltitle + tr( "\nVbar vs Mol. Weight" );
10216  yatitle = tr( "Vbar at 20" ) + DEGC;
10217  xatitle = tr( "Molecular Weight" );
10218  }
10219 
10220  else if ( type == 7 )
10221  {
10222  pltitle = pltitle + tr( "\nDiff. Coeff. vs Sed. Coeff." );
10223  yatitle = tr( "Diff. Coeff. D20,W" );
10224  xatitle = tr( "Sedimentation Coefficient s20,W" );
10225  }
10226 
10227  else if ( type == 8 )
10228  {
10229  pltitle = pltitle + tr( "\nDiff. Coeff. vs Molecular Weight" );
10230  yatitle = tr( "Diff. Coeff. D20,W" );
10231  xatitle = tr( "Molecular Weight" );
10232  }
10233 
10234  dataPlotClear( data_plot1 );
10235 
10236  data_plot1->setTitle( pltitle );
10237  data_plot1->setAxisTitle( QwtPlot::yLeft, yatitle );
10238  data_plot1->setAxisTitle( QwtPlot::xBottom, xatitle );
10239 
10240  QwtPlotGrid* data_grid = us_grid( data_plot1 );
10241  QwtPlotCurve* data_curv = us_curve( data_plot1, "distro" );
10242  QwtSymbol* symbol = new QwtSymbol;
10243 
10244  int dsize = model_used.components.size();
10245  QVector< double > vecx( dsize );
10246  QVector< double > vecy( dsize );
10247  double* xx = vecx.data();
10248  double* yy = vecy.data();
10249  double xmin = 1.0e30;
10250  double xmax = -1.0e30;
10251  double ymin = 1.0e30;
10252  double ymax = -1.0e30;
10253  double xval;
10254  double yval;
10255  double rdif;
10256 
10257  for ( int jj = 0; jj < dsize; jj++ )
10258  {
10259  xval = ( ( type & 1 ) == 1 ) ? model_used.components[ jj ].s :
10260  model_used.components[ jj ].mw;
10261 
10262  if ( type < 5 ) yval = model_used.components[ jj ].f_f0;
10263  else if ( type < 7 ) yval = model_used.components[ jj ].vbar20;
10264  else yval = model_used.components[ jj ].D;
10265 
10266  xx[ jj ] = xval;
10267  yy[ jj ] = yval;
10268  xmin = min( xval, xmin );
10269  xmax = max( xval, xmax );
10270  ymin = min( yval, ymin );
10271  ymax = max( yval, ymax );
10272  }
10273 
10274  rdif = ( xmax - xmin ) / 20.0;
10275  xmin -= rdif;
10276  xmax += rdif;
10277  rdif = ( ymax - ymin ) / 20.0;
10278  ymin -= rdif;
10279  ymax += rdif;
10280  xmin = ( type & 1 ) == 1 ? xmin : max( xmin, 0.0 );
10281  ymin = max( ymin, 0.0 );
10282 
10283  data_grid->enableYMin ( true );
10284  data_grid->enableY ( true );
10285  data_grid->setMajorPen(
10286  QPen( US_GuiSettings::plotMinGrid(), 0, Qt::DotLine ) );
10287 
10288  symbol->setStyle( QwtSymbol::Ellipse );
10289  symbol->setPen( QPen( Qt::red ) );
10290  symbol->setBrush( QBrush( Qt::yellow ) );
10291  if ( dsize > 100 )
10292  symbol->setSize( 5 );
10293  else if ( dsize > 50 )
10294  symbol->setSize( 8 );
10295  else if ( dsize > 20 )
10296  symbol->setSize( 10 );
10297  else
10298  symbol->setSize( 12 );
10299 
10300  data_curv->setStyle ( QwtPlotCurve::NoCurve );
10301  data_curv->setSymbol ( symbol );
10302  data_curv->setSamples( xx, yy, dsize );
10303 
10304  data_plot1->setAxisAutoScale( QwtPlot::xBottom );
10305  data_plot1->setAxisAutoScale( QwtPlot::yLeft );
10306  data_plot1->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::xBottom, xmin, xmax );
10307  data_plot1->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::yLeft, ymin, ymax );
10308 
10309  data_plot1->replot();
10310 }

10312 // Create a subdirectory if need be
10313 bool US_ReporterGMP::mkdir( const QString& baseDir, const QString& subdir )
10314 {
10315  QDir folder( baseDir );
10316 
10317  if ( folder.exists( subdir ) ) return true;
10318 
10319  if ( folder.mkdir( subdir ) ) return true;
10320 
10321  QMessageBox::warning( this,
10322  tr( "File error" ),
10323  tr( "Could not create the directory:\n" ) + baseDir + "/" + subdir );
10324 
10325  return false;
10326 }

10328 // Write out a plot
10329 void US_ReporterGMP::write_plot( const QString& filename, const QwtPlot* plot )
10330 {

10337 
10338 // else if ( filename.endsWith( "rbitmap.png" ) )
10339 // { // Special case of rbitmap PNG
10340 // if ( rbmapd == 0 )

10342 // rbmapd = new US_ResidsBitmap( resids );

10344 // rbmapd->show();

10346 // }
10347 
10348 // else
10349 // { // if already displayed, replot and re-activate
10350 // rbmapd->replot( resids );
10351 // rbmapd->raise();
10352 // rbmapd->activateWindow();
10353 // }
10354 
10355 // #if QT_VERSION > 0x050000
10356 // QPixmap pixmap = ((QWidget*)rbmapd)->grab();
10357 // #else
10358 // QPixmap pixmap = QPixmap::grabWidget( rbmapd, 0, 0,
10359 // rbmapd->width(), rbmapd->height() );
10360 // #endif
10361 
10362 // if ( ! pixmap.save( filename ) )
10363 // QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "File Write Error" ),
10364 // tr( "Unable to write file" ) + filename );
10365 // }
10366 
10367  else if ( filename.endsWith( "3dplot.png" ) )
10368  { // Special case of 3dplot PNG
10369  // if ( eplotcd == 0 )

10380  bool ok = widgw->save_plot( filename, QString( "png" ) );

10389  if ( ! ok )
10390  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "File Write Error" ),
10391  tr( "Unable to write file" ) + filename );
10392  }
10393 
10394  else if ( filename.endsWith( ".png" ) )
10395  { // General case of PNG
10396  if ( US_GuiUtil::save_png( filename, plot ) != 0 )
10397  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "File Write Error" ),
10398  tr( "Unable to write file" ) + filename );
10399  }
10400 }

10412 // Update progress when thread reports
10413 void US_ReporterGMP::thread_progress( int thr, int icomp )
10414 {
10415  qDebug() << "Updating progress multiple threads, thr, icomp -- " << thr << icomp;
10416  int kcomp = 0;
10417  kcomps[ thr ] = icomp;
10418  for ( int ii = 0; ii < nthread; ii++ )
10419  kcomp += kcomps[ ii ];
10420  progress_msg->setValue( kcomp );
10421  qApp->processEvents();
10422  qDebug() << "THR PROGR thr icomp" << thr << icomp << "kcomp" << kcomp;
10423 }
10424 
10425 
10426 // Update count of threads completed and colate simulations when all are done
10427 void US_ReporterGMP::thread_complete( int thr )
10428 {
10429  thrdone++;
10430  qDebug() << "THR COMPL thr" << thr << "thrdone" << thrdone;
10431 
10432  if ( thrdone >= nthread )
10433  { // All threads are done, so sum thread simulation data
10434  for ( int ii = 0; ii < sdata->scanData.size(); ii++ )
10435  {
10436  for ( int jj = 0; jj < sdata->xvalues.size(); jj++ )
10437  {
10438  //double conc = 0.0;
10439  double conc = sdata->value( ii, jj );
10440 
10441  for ( int kk = 0; kk < nthread; kk++ )
10442  conc += tsimdats[ kk ].value( ii, jj );
10443 
10444  sdata->setValue( ii, jj, conc );
10445  }
10446  }
10447 
10448  // Then show the results
10449  show_results( triple_info_map );
10450  }
10451 }
10452 
10453 // Adjust model components based on buffer, vbar, and temperature
10454 void US_ReporterGMP::adjustModel( )
10455 {
10456  model = model_used;
10457 
10458  // build model component correction factors
10459  double avgTemp = edata->average_temperature();
10460  double vbar20 = svbar_global.toDouble();
10461 
10462  solution.density = density;
10463  solution.viscosity = viscosity;
10464  solution.manual = manual;
10465  solution.vbar20 = vbar20;
10466  solution.vbar = US_Math2::calcCommonVbar( solution_rec, avgTemp );
10467 // solution.vbar = US_Math2::adjust_vbar20( solution.vbar20, avgTemp );
10468 
10469  US_Math2::data_correction( avgTemp, solution );
10470 
10471  double scorrec = solution.s20w_correction;
10472  double dcorrec = solution.D20w_correction;
10473  double mc_vbar = model.components[ 0 ].vbar20;
10474  // Set constant-vbar and constant-ff0 flags
10475  cnstvb = model.constant_vbar();
10476  cnstff = model.constant_ff0();
10477 
10478  US_Math2::SolutionData sd;
10479  sd.density = solution.density;
10480  sd.viscosity = solution.viscosity;
10481  sd.vbar20 = solution.vbar20;
10482  sd.vbar = solution.vbar;
10483  sd.manual = solution.manual;
10484  qDebug() << "Fem:Adj: avgT" << avgTemp << "scorr dcorr" << scorrec << dcorrec;
10485 
10486  if ( cnstvb && mc_vbar != sd.vbar20 && mc_vbar != 0.0 )
10487  { // Use vbar from the model component, instead of from the solution
10488  sd.vbar20 = mc_vbar;
10489  sd.vbar = US_Math2::adjust_vbar20( sd.vbar20, avgTemp );
10490  US_Math2::data_correction( avgTemp, sd );
10491  scorrec = sd.s20w_correction;
10492  dcorrec = sd.D20w_correction;
10493  qDebug() << "Fem:Adj: cnstvb" << cnstvb << " scorr dcorr" << scorrec << dcorrec;
10494  }
10495  qDebug() << "Fem:Adj: avgT" << avgTemp << "vb20 vb" << sd.vbar20 << sd.vbar;
10496 
10497  // Convert to experiment space: adjust s,D based on solution,temperature
10498 
10499  for ( int jj = 0; jj < model.components.size(); jj++ )
10500  {
10501  US_Model::SimulationComponent* sc = &model.components[ jj ];
10502 
10503  sc->vbar20 = ( sc->vbar20 == 0.0 ) ? vbar20 : sc->vbar20;
10504 
10505  if ( ! cnstvb )
10506  { // Set s,D corrections based on component vbar
10507  sd.vbar20 = sc->vbar20;
10508  sd.vbar = US_Math2::adjust_vbar20( sd.vbar20, avgTemp );
10509  US_Math2::data_correction( avgTemp, sd );
10510  scorrec = sd.s20w_correction;
10511  dcorrec = sd.D20w_correction;
10512  }
10513 
10514 double s20w=sc->s;
10515 double d20w=sc->D;
10516  sc->s /= scorrec;
10517  sc->D /= dcorrec;
10518  qDebug() << "Fem:Adj: s20w D20w" << s20w << d20w
10519  << "s D" << sc->s << sc->D << " jj" << jj << "vb20 vb" << sc->vbar20 << sd.vbar;
10520 
10521  if ( sc->extinction > 0.0 )
10522  sc->molar_concentration = sc->signal_concentration / sc->extinction;
10523  }
10524 
10525 }

10528 //Parse filename and extract one for given optics type in combined runs
10529 QString US_ReporterGMP::get_filename( QString triple_name )
10530 {
10531  qDebug() << "FileName -- " << FileName;
10532  qDebug() << "triple_name -- " << triple_name;
10533 
10534  QString filename_parsed;
10535 
10536  if ( FileName.contains(",") && FileName.contains("IP") && FileName.contains("RI") )
10537  {
10538  QStringList fileList = FileName.split(",");
10539 
10540  //Interference
10541  if ( triple_name.contains("Interference") )
10542  {
10543  for (int i=0; i<fileList.size(); ++i )
10544  {
10545  QString fname = fileList[i];
10546  int pos = fname.lastIndexOf(QChar('-'));
10547  qDebug() << "IP: pos -- " << pos;
10548  qDebug() << "IP: fname.mid( pos ) -- " << fname.mid( pos );
10549  if ( fname.mid( pos ) == "-IP")
10550  {
10551  filename_parsed = fname;
10552  break;
10553  }
10554  }
10555  }
10556  //UV/vis.
10557  else
10558  {
10559  for (int i=0; i<fileList.size(); ++i )
10560  {
10561  QString fname = fileList[i];
10562  int pos = fname.lastIndexOf(QChar('-'));
10563  qDebug() << "RI: pos -- " << pos;
10564  qDebug() << "RI: fname.mid( pos ) -- " << fname.mid( pos );
10565  if ( fname.mid( pos ) == "-RI")
10566  {
10567  filename_parsed = fname;
10568  break;
10569  }
10570  }
10571  }
10572  }
10573  else
10574  filename_parsed = FileName;
10575 
10576  qDebug() << "Parsed filename: " << filename_parsed;
10577 
10578  return filename_parsed;
10579 }

12036 double US_ReporterGMP::mmToPixels(QPrinter& printer, int mm)
12037 {
12038  return mm * 0.039370147 * printer.resolution();
12039 }
12040 
12041 void US_ReporterGMP::printDocument(QPrinter& printer, QTextDocument* doc) //, QWidget* parentWidget)
12042 {
12043  int textMargins = 12; // in millimeters
12044  //int textMargins = 0; // in millimeters
12045 
12046  QPainter painter( &printer );
12047  QSizeF pageSize = printer.pageRect().size(); // page size in pixels
12048  // Calculate the rectangle where to lay out the text
12049  const double tm = mmToPixels(printer, textMargins);
12050  const qreal footerHeight = painter.fontMetrics().height();
12051  const QRectF textRect(tm, tm, pageSize.width() - 2 * tm, pageSize.height() - 2 * tm - footerHeight);
12052  qDebug() << "textRect=, width, height: " << textRect << textRect.width() << textRect.height();
12053  qDebug() << "footerHeigh: " << footerHeight;
12054  doc->setPageSize(textRect.size());
12055 
12056  const int pageCount = doc->pageCount();
12057  // QProgressDialog dialog( QObject::tr( "Printing" ), QObject::tr( "Cancel" ), 0, pageCount, parentWidget );
12058  // dialog.setWindowModality( Qt::ApplicationModal );
12059  progress_msg = new QProgressDialog ("Preparing .PDF...", QString(), 0, pageCount, this);
12060  progress_msg->setWindowFlags(Qt::Tool | Qt::WindowTitleHint | Qt::CustomizeWindowHint);
12061  progress_msg->setModal( true );
12062  progress_msg->setWindowTitle(tr("Printing..."));
12063  QFont font_d = progress_msg->property("font").value<QFont>();
12064  QFontMetrics fm(font_d);
12065  int pixelsWide = fm.width( progress_msg->windowTitle() );
12066  qDebug() << "Progress_msg: pixelsWide -- " << pixelsWide;
12067  progress_msg ->setMinimumWidth( pixelsWide*2 );
12068  progress_msg->adjustSize();
12069  progress_msg->setAutoClose( false );
12070  progress_msg->setValue( 0 );
12071  progress_msg->show();
12072  qApp->processEvents();
12073 
12074  bool firstPage = true;
12075  for (int pageIndex = 0; pageIndex < pageCount; ++pageIndex)
12076  {
12077  progress_msg->setValue( pageIndex );
12078 
12079  if (!firstPage)
12080  {
12081  //immediately before newPage, set new margins:
12082  //printer.setPageMargins(0, -15, 0, -15, QPrinter::Millimeter);
12083  printer.newPage();
12084  }
12085 
12086  paintPage( printer, pageIndex, pageCount, &painter, doc, textRect, footerHeight );
12087  firstPage = false;
12088  }
12089 
12090  qApp->processEvents();
12091  progress_msg->close();
12092  qApp->processEvents();
12093 }
12094 
12095 
12096 void US_ReporterGMP::paintPage(QPrinter& printer, int pageNumber, int pageCount,
12097  QPainter* painter, QTextDocument* doc,
12098  const QRectF& textRect, qreal footerHeight )
12099 {
12100  int borderMargins = 10; // in millimeters
12101  qDebug() << "Printing page" << pageNumber;
12102  const QSizeF pageSize = printer.paperRect().size();
12103  qDebug() << "pageSize=" << pageSize;
12104  qDebug() << "printerResolution=" << printer.resolution();
12105 
12106  // const double bm = mmToPixels(printer, borderMargins);
12107  // const QRectF borderRect(bm, bm, pageSize.width() - 2 * bm, pageSize.height() - 2 * bm);
12108  //painter->drawRect(borderRect);
12109 
12110  painter->save();
12111 
12112  // textPageRect is the rectangle in the coordinate system of the QTextDocument, in pixels,
12113  // and starting at (0,0) for the first page. Second page is at y=doc->pageSize().height().
12114  const QRectF textPageRect(0, pageNumber * doc->pageSize().height(), doc->pageSize().width(), doc->pageSize().height());
12115  // Clip the drawing so that the text of the other pages doesn't appear in the margins
12116  //painter->setClipRect(textRect);
12117  // Translate so that 0,0 is now the page corner
12118  painter->translate(0, -textPageRect.top());
12119  // Translate so that 0,0 is the text rect corner
12120  painter->translate(textRect.left(), textRect.top());
12121 
12122  // qDebug() << "Painter's settings: font, metrics -- "
12123  // << painter->fontMetrics()
12124  // << painter->fontInfo()
12125  // << painter->font();
12126 
12127  qDebug() << "Painter's settings: font, metrics -- "
12128  << painter->fontInfo().family()
12129  << painter->fontInfo().pointSizeF()
12130  << painter->fontInfo().pointSize();
12131 
12132  doc->drawContents(painter,textPageRect); //add second params, OR it appears to draw full QTextDoc.... (huge sizes)
12133  painter->restore();
12134 
12135  // Footer: e-Signer comment && page number
12136  QRectF footerRect = textRect;
12137  footerRect.setTop(textRect.bottom());
12138  footerRect.setHeight( 1*footerHeight ); //will a parameter on #of lines (footer height, depending on # reviewers...)
12139  //test below
12140  //footerRect.setHeight( 4*footerHeight ); //will a parameter on #of lines (footer height, depending on # reviewers...)
12141  //end test
12142 
12143  painter->setPen(Qt::blue);
12144  QFont pfont = painter -> font();
12145  qDebug() << "Paint page: painter: pixelSize(), pointSize() -- "
12146  << pfont. pixelSize()
12147  << pfont. pointSize();
12148  int original_pfont_size = pfont. pointSize();
12149  pfont. setPointSize( int ( original_pfont_size * 0.8 ) );
12150  painter-> setFont(pfont);
12151 
12152  QString init_footer;
12153  init_footer = auto_mode ? "Not e-Signed/Not Reviewed..." : "Custom Report";
12154  //painter->drawText(footerRect, Qt::AlignLeft, QObject::tr("Not e-Signed/Not Reviewed..." ));
12155  painter->drawText(footerRect, Qt::AlignLeft, init_footer );
12156  //test below
12157  //painter->drawText(footerRect, Qt::AlignLeft, QObject::tr("Not e-Signed/Not Reviewed...\nNot e-Signed/Not Reviewed...\nNot e-Signed/Not Reviewed...\nNot e-Signed/Not Reviewed..." ));
12158  //end test
12159  painter->drawText(footerRect, Qt::AlignVCenter | Qt::AlignRight, QObject::tr("Page %1/%2").arg(pageNumber+1).arg(pageCount));
12160 
12161  // Footer: page number or "end"
12162  // if (pageNumber == pageCount - 1)
12163  // painter->drawText(footerRect, Qt::AlignLeft, QObject::tr("Footer to be passed by e-Signers"));
12164  // else
12165  // painter->drawText(footerRect, Qt::AlignVCenter | Qt::AlignRight, QObject::tr("Page %1/%2").arg(pageNumber+1).arg(pageCount));
12166 
12167  //and restore painter's font:
12168  pfont. setPointSize( original_pfont_size );
12169  painter-> setFont(pfont);
12170 }

12414 //Pasre reportMask JSON
12415 void US_ReporterGMP::parse_edited_gen_mask_json( const QString maskJson, GenReportMaskStructure & MaskStr )
12416 {
12417  QJsonDocument jsonDoc = QJsonDocument::fromJson( maskJson.toUtf8() );
12418  QJsonObject json = jsonDoc.object();
12419 
12420  int has_sol_items = 0;
12421  int has_analysis_items = 0;
12422 
12423  MaskStr.ShowReportParts .clear();
12424  MaskStr.ShowSolutionParts .clear();
12425  MaskStr.ShowAnalysisGenParts .clear();
12426  MaskStr.ShowAnalysis2DSAParts.clear();
12427  MaskStr.ShowAnalysisPCSAParts.clear();
12428  MaskStr.has_anagen_items = 0;
12429  MaskStr.has_ana2dsa_items = 0;
12430  MaskStr.has_anapcsa_items = 0;
12431 
12432  foreach(const QString& key, json.keys())
12433  {
12434  QJsonValue value = json.value(key);
12435  qDebug() << "Key = " << key << ", Value = " << value;//.toString();
12436 
12437  if ( value.isString() )
12438  {
12439  if ( value.toString().toInt() )
12440  MaskStr.ShowReportParts[ key ] = true;
12441  else
12442  MaskStr.ShowReportParts[ key ] = false;
12443  }
12444  else if ( value.isArray() )
12445  MaskStr.ShowReportParts[ key ] = true; //for now
12446 
12447  //treat Solutions && Analysis: nested JSON
12448  if ( key.contains("Solutions") || key.contains("Analysis") )
12449  {
12450  QJsonArray json_array = value.toArray();
12451  for (int i=0; i < json_array.size(); ++i )
12452  {
12453  foreach(const QString& array_key, json_array[i].toObject().keys())
12454  {
12455  if ( key.contains("Solutions") )
12456  {
12457 
12458  qDebug() << "Parse_editedJsonGen: Solution: array_key, value: "
12459  << array_key
12460  << json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
12461 
12462 
12463  MaskStr.ShowSolutionParts[ array_key ] = json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toString();
12464  if ( MaskStr.ShowSolutionParts[ array_key ].toInt() )
12465  ++has_sol_items;
12466  }
12467  if ( key.contains("Analysis") )
12468  {
12469  QJsonObject newObj = json_array[i].toObject().value(array_key).toObject();
12470 
12471  foreach ( const QString& n_key, newObj.keys() )
12472  {
12473  QString analysis_cathegory_item_value = newObj.value( n_key ).toString();
12474 
12475  if ( analysis_cathegory_item_value.toInt() )
12476  ++has_analysis_items;
12477 
12478  if ( array_key.contains("General") )
12479  {
12480  MaskStr.ShowAnalysisGenParts[ n_key ] = analysis_cathegory_item_value;
12481  if ( MaskStr.ShowAnalysisGenParts[ n_key ].toInt() )
12482  ++MaskStr.has_anagen_items;
12483 
12484  qDebug() << "Parse_editedJsonGen: Analysis:Gen: n_key, value: "
12485  << n_key
12486  << MaskStr.ShowAnalysisGenParts[ n_key ];
12487 
12488  }
12489 
12490  if ( array_key.contains("2DSA") )
12491  {
12492  MaskStr.ShowAnalysis2DSAParts[ n_key ] = analysis_cathegory_item_value;
12493  if ( MaskStr.ShowAnalysis2DSAParts[ n_key ].toInt() )
12494  ++MaskStr.has_ana2dsa_items;
12495 
12496  qDebug() << "Parse_editedJsonGen: Analysis:2DSA: n_key, value: "
12497  << n_key
12498  << MaskStr.ShowAnalysis2DSAParts[ n_key ];
12499 
12500  }
12501 
12502  if ( array_key.contains("PCSA") )
12503  {
12504  MaskStr.ShowAnalysisPCSAParts[ n_key ] = analysis_cathegory_item_value;
12505  if ( MaskStr.ShowAnalysisPCSAParts[ n_key ].toInt() )
12506  ++MaskStr.has_anapcsa_items;
12507 
12508  qDebug() << "Parse_editedJsonGen: Analysis:PCSA: n_key, value: "
12509  << n_key
12510  << MaskStr.ShowAnalysisPCSAParts[ n_key ];
12511  }
12512  }
12513  }
12514  }
12515  }
12516 
12517  //Set if to show "Solutions" based on children items
12518  if ( key.contains("Solutions") && !has_sol_items )
12519  MaskStr.ShowReportParts[ key ] = false;
12520 
12521  if ( key.contains("Analysis") && !has_analysis_items )
12522  MaskStr.ShowReportParts[ key ] = false;
12523  }
12524  }
12525 }

12685  triple_name += "Interference";
12686  else
12687  triple_name += array_key.split(" ")[0];
12688 
12689 
12690  QString model_name = n_key.split(" ")[0];
12691  MaskStr.ShowTripleModelPseudo3dParts[ triple_name ][ model_name ][ p_key ] = feature_pseudo3d_value;
12692  if ( MaskStr.ShowTripleModelPseudo3dParts[ triple_name ][ model_name ][ p_key ].toInt() )
12693  ++MaskStr.has_tripleModelPseudo3d_items[ triple_name ][ model_name ];
12694 
12695  qDebug() << "Parse_editedJsonTriples: triple_name: " << triple_name << ": "
12696  << "model_name, j_key, p_key, feature_PSEUDO_value: "
12697  << model_name
12698  << j_key
12699  << p_key
12700  << feature_pseudo3d_value;
12701  }
12702  }
12703  //end of "Pseudo3D"
12704 
12705  //begin "Individual"
12706  else if ( j_key.contains("Individual") )
12707  {
12708  QJsonObject indComboObj = modelObj.value( j_key ).toObject();
12709 
12710  foreach ( const QString& p_key, indComboObj.keys() ) //over type[ranges], per model/per triple/per channel
12711  {
12712  QString feature_indCombo_value = indComboObj.value( p_key ).toString();
12713 
12714  //QString triple_name = key.split(" ")[1].split("-")[0] + array_key.split(" ")[0];
12715  QString triple_name = key.split(" ")[1].split("-")[0];
12716 
12717  if ( key.contains( "Interf" ) )
12718  triple_name += "Interference";
12719  else
12720  triple_name += array_key.split(" ")[0];
12721 
12722  QString model_name = n_key.split(" ")[0];
12723 
12724  MaskStr.ShowTripleTypeModelRangeIndividualCombo[ triple_name ][ model_name ][ p_key ] = feature_indCombo_value;
12725  if ( MaskStr.ShowTripleTypeModelRangeIndividualCombo[ triple_name ][ model_name ][ p_key ].toInt() )
12726  ++MaskStr.has_tripleModelIndCombo_items[ triple_name ][ model_name ];
12727 
12728  qDebug() << "Parse_editedJsonTriples: triple_name: " << triple_name << ": "
12729  << "model_name, j_key, p_key, feature_INDCOMBO_value: "
12730  << model_name
12731  << j_key
12732  << p_key
12733  << feature_indCombo_value;
12734  }
12735  }
12736  //end of "Individual"
12737  }
12738  }
12739  }
12740  }
12741  }
12742 
12743  if ( !has_channel_items )
12744  MaskStr.ShowChannelParts[ key ] = false;
12745  }
12746 }

12787 
12788 void US_ReporterGMP::get_children_to_json( QString& mask_edited, QTreeWidgetItem* item )
12789 {
12790  for( int i = 0; i < item->childCount(); ++i )
12791  {
12792  mask_edited += "\"" + item->child(i)->text(1).trimmed() + "\":";
12793 
12794  int children_lev2 = item->child(i)->childCount();
12795  if ( !children_lev2 )
12796  {
12797  mask_edited += "\"" + QString::number( int(item->child(i)->checkState(0)) ) + "\"";
12798  if ( i != item->childCount()-1 )
12799  mask_edited += ",";
12800  }
12801  else
12802  {
12803  mask_edited += "{";
12804  get_children_to_json( mask_edited, item->child(i) );
12805  mask_edited += "},";
12806  }
12807  }
12808 
12809  //ALEXEY: <-- little trick to enable super-fast recursive over arbitrary tree:))
12810  mask_edited.replace(",},","},");
12811 }
12812 
12813 
12814 //transform arbitrary-level tree to JSON
12815 QString US_ReporterGMP::tree_to_json( QMap < QString, QTreeWidgetItem * > topLevItems )
12816 {
12817  QString mask_edited;
12818  mask_edited += "{";
12819 
12820  QMap < QString, QTreeWidgetItem * >::iterator top;
12821  for ( top = topLevItems.begin(); top != topLevItems.end(); ++top )
12822  {
12823  mask_edited += "\"" + top.key().trimmed() + "\":";
12824  int children_lev1 = top.value()->childCount();
12825  if ( !children_lev1 )
12826  {
12827  mask_edited += "\"" + QString::number( int(top.value()->checkState(0)) ) + "\",";
12828  }
12829  else
12830  {
12831  mask_edited += "[{";
12832 
12833  //here we need to generalize for any tree nestedness: recursive
12834  get_children_to_json( mask_edited, top.value() );
12835 
12836  mask_edited += "}],";
12837  }
12838  }
12839 
12840 
12841  //ALEXEY: <-- little trick to enable super-fast recursive over arbitrary tree:))
12842  mask_edited.replace(",}],","}],");
12843  QString to_replace = "}],";
12844  QString new_substr = "}]";
12845  if ( ! mask_edited.mid( mask_edited.lastIndexOf( to_replace ) + to_replace.size(), mask_edited.length() ) .contains( "\"" ) )
12846  mask_edited.replace( mask_edited.lastIndexOf( to_replace ), to_replace.size(), new_substr );
12847 
12848  mask_edited += "}";
12849  mask_edited.replace( ",}", "}" );
12850 
12851  qDebug() << "Edited Mask: " << mask_edited;
12852 
12853  return mask_edited;
12854 }

13056 //Fetch Solution details && add to html_solutions
13057 void US_ReporterGMP::add_solution_details( const QString sol_id, const QString sol_comment, QString& html_solutions )
13058 {
13059  //get Solution info by ID:
13060  US_Passwd pw;
13061  QString masterPW = pw.getPasswd();
13062  US_DB2 db( masterPW );
13063 
13064  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
13065  {
13066  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Database Problem" ),
13067  tr( "Database returned the following error: \n" ) + db.lastError() );
13068 
13069  return;
13070  }
13071 
13072  US_Solution* solution = new US_Solution;
13073  int solutionID = sol_id.toInt();
13074 
13075  int status = US_DB2::OK;
13076  status = solution->readFromDB ( solutionID, &db );
13077 
13078  // Error reporting
13079  if ( status == US_DB2::NO_BUFFER )
13080  {
13081  QMessageBox::information( this,
13082  tr( "Attention" ),
13083  tr( "The buffer this solution refers to was not found.\n"
13084  "Please restore and try again.\n" ) );
13085  }
13086 
13087  else if ( status == US_DB2::NO_ANALYTE )
13088  {
13089  QMessageBox::information( this,
13090  tr( "Attention" ),
13091  tr( "One of the analytes this solution refers to was not found.\n"
13092  "Please restore and try again.\n" ) );
13093  }
13094 
13095  else if ( status != US_DB2::OK )
13096  {
13097  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Database Problem" ),
13098  tr( "Database returned the following error: \n" ) + db.lastError() );
13099  }
13100  //End of reading Solution:
13101 
13102  //add general solution details to html_solutions string:
13103  html_solutions += tr(
13104  "<table style=\"margin-left:5px\">"
13105  "<caption align=left> <b><i>Solution Information </i></b> </caption>"
13106  "</table>"
13107 
13108  "<table style=\"margin-left:20px\">"
13109  "<tr><td> Solution Name: </td> <td> %1 </td> </tr>"
13110  "<tr><td> Solution Comment: </td> <td> %2 </td> </tr>"
13111  "<tr><td> Common VBar (20&#8451;):</td> <td> %3 </td> </tr>"
13112  "<tr><td> Storage Temperature (&#8451;):</td><td> %4 </td> </tr>"
13113  "</table>"
13114  )
13115  .arg( solution->solutionDesc ) //1
13116  .arg( sol_comment ) //2
13117  .arg( QString::number( solution->commonVbar20 )) //3
13118  .arg( QString::number( solution->storageTemp )) //4
13119  ;
13120 
13121 
13122  //Get analytes information
13123  if ( genMask_edited.ShowSolutionParts[ "Analyte Information" ].toInt() )
13124  {
13125  html_solutions += tr(
13126  "<table style=\"margin-left:20px\">"
13127  "<caption align=left> <b><i>Analytes Information</i></b> </caption>"
13128  "</table>"
13129  )
13130  ;
13131  }
13132 
13133  QString analyte_gen_info;
13134  QString analyte_detailed_info;
13135  int num_analytes = solution->analyteInfo.size();
13136  for (int i=0; i < num_analytes; ++i )
13137  {
13138  //clear analyte's strings:
13139  analyte_gen_info = QString("");
13140  analyte_detailed_info = QString("");
13141 
13142 
13143  US_Analyte analyte = solution->analyteInfo[ i ].analyte;
13144  QString a_name = analyte.description;
13145  QString a_amount = QString::number( solution->analyteInfo[ i ].amount );
13146 
13147  analyte_gen_info += tr(
13148  "<tr>"
13149  "<td> <i>Analyte #%1: </i></td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "
13150  "<td> Name: </td> <td> %2</td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"
13151  "<td> Molar Ratio:</td> <td>%3</td>"
13152  "</tr>"
13153  )
13154  .arg( QString::number( i + 1 ) ) //1
13155  .arg( a_name ) //2
13156  .arg( a_amount ) //3
13157  ;
13158 
13159  QString a_mw = QString::number( analyte.mw ) + " D";
13160  QString a_vbar20 = QString::number( analyte.vbar20 );
13161 
13162  int seqlen = analyte.sequence.length();
13163  QString seqsmry = analyte.sequence;
13164  int total = 0;
13165 
13166  if ( seqlen == 0 )
13167  seqsmry = tr( "(empty)" );
13168  else
13169  {
13170  seqsmry = seqsmry.toLower()
13171  .remove( QRegExp( "[\\s0-9]" ) );
13172  seqlen = seqsmry.length();
13173  if ( seqlen > 25 )
13174  {
13175  seqsmry = QString( seqsmry ).left( 10 ) + " ... "
13176  + QString( seqsmry ).mid( seqlen - 10 );
13177  }
13178  //seqsmry += "\n ";
13179  seqsmry += "<br> ";
13180 
13181  for ( int ii = 0; ii < 26; ii++ )
13182  {
13183  QString letter = QString( QChar( 'a' + ii ) );
13184  int lcount = analyte.sequence.count( letter );
13185  total += lcount;
13186  if ( lcount > 0 )
13187  {
13188  seqsmry += QString().sprintf( "%d", lcount )
13189  + " " + letter.toUpper() + ", ";
13190  //seqsmry += "\n ";
13191  }
13192  }
13193  seqsmry += QString().sprintf( "%d", total ) + " tot";
13194  }
13195 
13196  QString a_type = tr( "Carbohydrate/Other" );
13197  a_type = analyte.type == ( US_Analyte::PROTEIN ) ? tr( "Protein" ) : a_type;
13198  a_type = analyte.type == ( US_Analyte::DNA ) ? tr( "DNA" ) : a_type;
13199  a_type = analyte.type == ( US_Analyte::RNA ) ? tr( "RNA" ) : a_type;
13200 
13201  //absorbing residues
13202  US_Math2::Peptide p;
13203  US_Math2::calc_vbar( p, analyte.sequence, 20.0 );
13204  analyte.mw = ( analyte.mw == 0.0 ) ? p.mw : analyte.mw;
13205 
13206  // Absorbing residues
13207  int cys = int(p.c);
13208  int hao = int(p.j);
13209  int orn = int(p.o);
13210  int trp = int(p.w);
13211  int tyr = int(p.y);
13212  int all_abs = 0;
13213  all_abs = cys + hao + orn + trp + tyr;
13214  qDebug() << "Tot AAs: " << all_abs;
13215  QString absorbing_residues = tr( "(empty)" );
13216  if (all_abs > 0)
13217  {
13218  absorbing_residues = "";
13219  if ( cys > 0)
13220  absorbing_residues += QString().sprintf( "%d", cys ) + " " + "Cys" + ", ";
13221  if ( hao > 0)
13222  absorbing_residues += QString().sprintf( "%d", hao ) + " " + "Hao" + ", ";
13223  if ( orn > 0)
13224  absorbing_residues += QString().sprintf( "%d", orn ) + " " + "Orn" + ", ";
13225  if ( trp > 0)
13226  absorbing_residues += QString().sprintf( "%d", trp ) + " " + "Trp" + ", ";
13227  if ( tyr > 0)
13228  absorbing_residues += QString().sprintf( "%d", tyr ) + " " + "Tyr" + ", ";
13229 
13230  absorbing_residues += QString().sprintf( "%d", all_abs ) + " tot";
13231  }
13232
